text:
【『宗教問題』24号が発刊】

先月末に『宗教問題』24号が発刊され、宗教問題社より御恵贈戴いた。

今号の特集は「宗教界からの#metoo」と分析特集「池田大作『人間革命』の完結」の２部構成からなる。

前者は宗教界でのセクハラ、或いは、性犯罪について論及したものであり、後者は『新・人間革命』の完結をうけての分析である。

今号では連載「日興と池田大作をつなぐものー日興門流の思想と展開」に加え、分析特集でも「『人間革命』はその完結により「現代の御書」たる性格を強くした」を執筆した。

連載「日興と池田大作をつなぐものー日興門流の思想と展開」では日興の譲状として『日興跡条々事』について論及した。
日興文書についての論及は今号で終え、次号からは日興の教学思想について論及していく。

終幕はまだまだ先のことになるが、最後までお付き合い戴ければ幸甚です。

text:
out of sight out of mind right? well that is exactly the reason my posts will be starting to get a little more hard to see. because i believe the hard, sad, disgusting things need to be seen in order to have real hope for a real change in this cruel world. i’ve had a hand full of people just in the past week message me and tell me they are thinking about going vegan and that my posts break their hearts... as they should! there is nothing wrong with you because these type of posts break your heart! it means you have compassion within you! it means you deep down know what is right and what is wrong! my posts may suck! but imagine how bad the lives of these poor innocent souls suck! if this is hard for you to see, look harder and longer, look into their eyes and think about the horrors they see and go through before they experience their unfair and brutal deaths! stop thinking about going vegan and just do it. stop making excuses on how hard it is to go vegan because it’s not! break your habits of eating shit, puss and flesh. change the way your babies and children grow up so they don’t have to make the change when they are older. you teach your children to love and be gentle towards animals but then you feed them “happy meals” and hot dogs! stop and think about the terror in their little faces if they actually knew what they were eating. if they saw the photos of the same animals they love being killed. i will not apologize if my posts are getting to you because that is exactly my goal. i’m an animal activist. i have chosen to be their voice!
・・・
rp @estherveganlin if people saw the faces and stories who their eating .. most people would feel sick, sad and disgusted not hungry.a huge majority wouldn't be able to stomach the hard truth of who their food was.because naturally we are compassionate beings and biologically herbivores choose compassion go vegan #respectlife #loveanimals #letthembe #theirlivesmatter #lovethemall #animallovers #animalkingdom #familyiseverything #savetheocean #savetheearth #peaceandlove #govegan #crueltyfree #environment #environmentalist #planetearth #metoo #wildlife #animalshaverights #proteina #babyanimals #donttakeourplanetforgranted

text:
dec 6. day of remembrance. 
i have been extremely open about how i did not get justice when i was raped at 18. i turned that into @projectfword. i've been working with sex offenders now for years. it became my way of creating purpose out of trauma.

but on sept 12 2017, i was at a pub and was sexually assaulted again. again. in public. brazen. by a stranger. i was wearing nothing cute - it wasnt late and i wasnt drunk. again. (all of the reasons people say we are assaulted)
earlier this month, i posted that i went to court and faced the man who assaulted me. everyone said they were happy i finally found justice from the original assault --- i didnt. it was another case. 
i stayed quiet about what i was going through because many people close to me were watching all of the public #metoo cases and making horrific judgements on all ends. for the first time in my life, i felt ashamed of being a victim. 
how could this happen to me again?

i guess there is a bright side which is that i did receive "justice" in the sense that i was believed. and this is only because the brazen assault was on surveillance camera. clear.
but the entire court process was hell. i know why women dont speak up.

however - i've been doing work along the way with counselors and social workers from women's college hospital who have 10+ years experience. my case was the first case they worked where there was a 'guilty' outcome. please take that in. 
this last year almost broke me. why do i want to live in this world when this is the reality?
only 5% of sexual assaults are reported and less than half move forward. less than half of that is found in a guilty verdict. 
around 1% of all sexual assault cases ever receive court "justice". we are your friends, family, girlfriends, wives, sisters - please believe us. ..i wish i didnt have to believe it. 
my case goes to sentencing next week. authority gets to decide his punishment for my life being impacted. probably probation for me now being scared of public places. 
dec 6 is about acknowledging that we have a long way to go. i'll be spending the day recognizing the honoring the women in my life and i hope you do the same. 🌹

#dec6
#dayofremembrance

⠀
these days a lot of organizing groups aren't using the right crm* for their organizing needs. or they're overpaying for what they actually need. yet the tool that we rely on to hold our supporter data, send mass email, fundraise, and set up petitions and email actions to targets, is vital to the effectiveness of our organizing.⠀
⠀
use the free "whichcrm?" online tool to get started. complete the 30-question survey and you'll get a preliminary recommendation of which crm will likely best meet your needs. ⠀

text:
i love this verse, probably my most favoritist (😂 #momlife). the lord blessed me w this verse right before i was assaulted in high school. that moment in time changed my life forever and the lord knew how to reach out to me. it was the captain of the football team and i was ridiculed in school. but i was comforted w this verse. i would say it over and over and god gave me the peace and the strength to get through each day. .
.
god will do the same for you. he will reach out to you before you even know you need it. that’s how awesome our god is. god was there for me and blessing after blessing came. god wants to do the same for you friend.
.
.
.
.
.
#god #love #hope #nevergiveup #metoo #survivor #bible #bibleverse #godlovesyou

text:
protect your sister

january 1985
mommy (translated from polish):
“cindy it’s your job to watch over and protect your little sister”

october 2018:
voices in my head during meditation:
‘i have to do something. enough of this bullshit sexual violence. enough. what can i do? protect your sisters.’ both my little sister and my sisters are strong and powerful goddesses who i’ve learned so much from and don’t need me to protect them.

i don’t feel safe walking down the street sometimes and my martial arts training has made me feel safer and empowered. 
i’m so excited to share what i’ve learned from fighting with my sisters this saturday 12/8 @earthartscenter so that my sisters can gain some tools to protect themselves.

#backtolife #fightlikeagirl #ilovedisney #muaythai #loveyourselffirst #earthartscenter #earth #disney #enoughisenough #metoo #icallbullshit #enough

text:
you have polluted my ecosystem
my air is contaminated
my rivers are blocked
my forests are ablaze 
but while i know your ruining of me was a cruel act
it was also a gift
now i have learned to care for my soil 
treat it with tenderness and care
and one day,
i will plant the seeds of strong oak trees
so the next time someone comes to tear me down 
or uproot my life
i will have no paths for destruction like you to wander down
(my original art & poem)
#recovery #mentalhealth #wellness #art #artjournal #poetry #poemsofinstagram #collage #mentalhealthawareness #metoo #poem #zines

text:
thank you @skc_london for hosting me last night. i talked about my journey with depression and an eating disorder and how i now lead hiking adventures in the himalayas, pyrenees and lake district to re-set the mind and body back to balance❤️🌲🌞🏔 .
re-connection to yourself, connection to each other, and connection to the beautiful dramatic nature being the healing factors to soothe the mind
.
it was my first public speaking event and makes chuckle, a few segway comments from the crowd added to the dynamic conversation around wellness and mental health...i blushed at times🤣. lots of lovely questions (and a nice space for my public speaking to improve 🙂). sharing vulnerabilities and fun times...have a tendency to over share naturally 😜☺️
.
graduated from @yogalondon yesterday too. gonna miss my yoga tribe and the seriously amazing girls i met. #yourvibeattractsyourtribe yesterday we all went round saying what lead us into yoga🤸🏼‍♂️🤔. for me, it’s to maintain ☯️balance☯️ with my mind and build strength and confidence in the body 💪🏼. yoga is healing for sooooo many people...it allows you to be in present moment for your class and not stuck in your head with uncomfortable thoughts. it was very inspiring hearing some vulnerabilities from people i perhaps thought had a very uncomplicated headspace. everyone struggles in their own way...it’s about shifting away from our destructive coping mechanisms and find soothing ones 🤸🏼‍♂️🎾🏓🛁🏃🏼‍♀️
.
🕉buddhism touts that suffering is an inevitable part of life but we can build strength in the mind on how we let it effect us🕉
.
with my yoga exams last week and early this week and the speech all done...it’s been an intense, inspiring, healing month and now time to uncoil and relax 🧘🏼‍♀️😴 (more the savasana emoji)
.
i’m gonna miss my yoga tribe 🎶scars to you’re beautful🎶 @alessiasmusic 
xxxxx

text:
last night in li a guy tried to run me down in his suv. he waited until i was in the crosswalk and then gunned for me. he was stopped at a stop sign. it was not an accident. i had to run out of the road, maybe missing the car by ten inches. when i turned around, he had braked hard in the intersection and turned around to grin at me. it was too dark to see his face. all i could catch was the glint of his teeth in the glare of a neighbour’s porch light, and a silhouette. in that moment, i had no idea if he was going to get out of the car and come after me. i didn’t know if he was armed. all i knew was that i was carrying two bags, and it was late, and it was dark, and the street was deserted. it was just me, and this silver suv, and a man who had just tried to kill me. (generously, shatter my ilium?)
.
i think the worst part about this is that this is so far from the worst thing that’s happened to me. i called the local police precinct, and they sent a car to meet me. i was still high on adrenaline when i gave them a statement. the white dude cop tried to calm me down, but of course i didn’t really feel safe with him either. i met him in the driveway because i didn’t want him in the house with my brother. he kept asking for a plate, which i didn’t have. the guy had sped off towards ocean ave. it was dark. does safe exist for qtpoc? for woc? for poc/pgm? what is “safe”? have any of us ever truly felt “safe”?
.
there is no happy ending or moral to this story. what i have to say is this: when women and femmes and nbs talk about being terrified of men, there is really no way for cis dudes to ever get what that’s like. what if he had a gun? i don’t fuckin’ know, man. this is our lives. all the time. i’m so tired of being tired of it all the time. i was two fuckin’ blocks from my ma’s place. if i can’t feel safe on my own street, i dunno where i can go. i don’t know. i don’t know, and so i keep trudging through the mire of shit. that’s what it feels like, on bad days. keep moving, because there’s nothing else we can do.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#fuck #violence #qtpoc #qpoc #lgbtq #queer #oneoffhem #assault #l4l #likeforlike #vineyard #sunset #nonbinary #nb #🌈 #metoo

text:
the mirror never lies adalah film fiksi arahan kamila andini pada tahun 2011. tahun ini datang kesempatan untuk kita menontonnya bersama sama!

hari: sabtu, 8 desember 2018
jam: registrasi dibuka mulai pukul 16.00 wita 
venue: lantai 2 warung @menbrayut
.
"clothes aren't going to change the world. the women who wear them will."
.
ada keterkaitan antara ruang hidupmu (lingkungan) dengan kehidupan juga penghidupan. fashion, baik baju maupun perhiasan adalah industri penghasil limbah yang besar bagi lingkungan. myra juliarti (desainer @akusiji) dan dian suri (desainer @kunangjewelry) memiliki kesamaan semangat dalam mengawali bisnisnya agar bertanggung jawab bagi lingkungan dan sosial.

ada cerita apa saja dari mereka? bagaimana tantangan yang ada dan apakah ada harapan terwujudnya revolusi fashion di masa kini?

dengarkan semuanya di #hearmetoo session setelah pemutaran. yuk berakhir pekan bersama enam belas film festival bali!

festival ini gratis dengan komitmen zerowaste, jadi bawa tumbler/botol minumnya ya!

text:
please join wgsssa on monday, dec 10th at 7:30 p.m. in the university theater (ut-108) for a free screening of the sundance documentary half the picture followed by a q&a with filmmaker amy adrion. 
half the picture celebrates the groundbreaking work of female film directors and investigates the systemic discrimination that has denied opportunities to many talented women in hollywood.  interviews with famous directors such as ava duvernay, jill soloway, lena dunham, catherine hardwicke and miranda july are complemented by expert analysis from the aclu’s melissa goodman, the sundance institute’s caroline libresco, vanity fair’s rebecca keegan, usc’s dr. stacy smith and san diego state university’s dr. martha lauzen.  an incredibly timely film in the #metoo and time's up era, half the picture is an inspiring account of the endurance of female talent in the face of hollywood bias.

text:
a fear of sharks is considered rational, when 1 in 262,365 will experience a shark attack.

1 in 6 women will experience rape or attempted rape, and being cautious of men is seen as misandry. 
further still, for every 1000 rapes, 994 will go unpunished.

all of a sudden the fear of dipping your toes in the water just got a whole lot closer to home. 
the #metoo movement brought to our attention how frequent, and just how many people we each know, to have been affected by rape, sexual abuse and unwanted advances. one is 43,728% more likely to be raped than to be attacked by a shark. 🦈 
#metoo #hearmetoo #womensrights #womensrightsdefenders #amnestyinternational #amnestyinternationalaustralia

text:
mensch sein...
.
der kabarettist volker pispers prägte den folgenden satz:
.
"ich bin die meiste zeit so sehr damit beschäftigt mensch zu sein, zum deutschsein komme ich nur ganz selten."
.
das wundervolle an diesem satz ist, dass man ihn auf tausend andere dinge übertragen kann, die uns in unserem alltag und zusammenleben oft und gerne mal im weg stehen.
.
wir denken, fühlen und leben eine kultur des trennens und abgrenzens - hier sind wir, dort sind die anderen. die unterschiedlichen länder und nationalitäten sind dafür nur eines von vielen beispielen - dort sind die deutschen, hier sind die schweizer und dort hinten sind noch franzosen, italiener und österreicher.
.
aber man muss gar nicht so weit gehen. die #metoo-dabatte hat einmal mehr aufgezeigt, wie tief allein schon die gräben sind, die nach wie vor zwischen mann und frau verlaufen. so viele unausgesprochene und ungelöste themen liegen dort seit jahrzehnten und jahrhunderten herum und lösen sich nur quälend langsam auf.
.
warum fällt es uns so schwer, auch mal eine verbindende, liebevolle und gütige haltung und sichtweise einzunehmen. für so eine haltung kann der gedanke von volker pispers eine wundervolle brücke sein. wir alle sind menschen... wir alle haben wünsche und bedürfnisse, sorgen, nöte und traurigkeiten. jeder von uns muss mal getröstet und in den arm genommen werden, jeder trägt seinen rucksack aus der vergangenheit, jeder fragt sich, was die zukunft bringt, jeder ist schon durch tiefe dunkle täler gewandert, wurde enttäuscht und verletzt - aber auch geliebt und aufgefangen. jeder ist auf seiner suche, nach seinem persönlichen sinn und zweck.
.
vor dem menschsein verblassen alle dinge, die uns scheinbar voneinander trennen. wer wirklich mensch sein möchte, für den spielen aspekte wie geschlecht, herkunft, sprache, alter, beruf oder religion keine rolle. warum auch?
.
das leben wird um einiges leichter und reicher, wenn wir uns daran ab und zu erinnern.
.
ich wünsche euch einen wunderschönen tag 💕💕💕
.
#mensch #sein #leben #wahrheit #weisheit #coaching #lebendig #inspiration #erkenntnis #spiritualität #yoga #schön #schönheit #ich #du #wir #gemeinsam #liebe #lieben #spirit #i #you #we #all

text:
hundreds of thousands of #metoo tweets are proof that sexual harassment at the workplace is alive and thriving. yet, in most of these cases, sexual harassers are let go with just a warning or worse, are treated as victims themselves.
.
it is an established fact that workplace sexual harassment is often more about the display of power and dominance over others than it is about sex. that means many sexual harassers could also be key employees at their organisations. so, it comes as a little surprise when many organisations prefer to protect these perpetrators because of business value instead of bringing them to task for their crime.
.
it’s time to stop this now. remember: supporting a criminal is nearly as bad as committing the crime itself. enough is enough. let’s stand in solidarity with the victims of sexual harassment from today. .
.

text:
en 2017, 265.000 personnes se sont déclarées victimes de violences sexuelles "hors ménage", c'est-à-dire que les actes commis ont été effectués par un tiers n'habitant pas avec elles. un chiffre en hausse par rapport à 2016 où elles étaient contre 173.000, selon une étude de l'observatoire national de la délinquance et des réponses pénales (ondrp) et de l'insee.
parmi ces victimes, 93.000 disent avoir subi un viol ou une tentative de viol, contre 58.000 en 2016. plus d’informations sur @rtl_girls et rtl.fr
.

text:
есть люди, которым удобно считать, что насилием можно считать только то, что оставляет синяки на теле. 
есть люди, которые считают, что сексуальным насилием можно считать только изнасилование. 
есть люди, которые полностью игнорируют те виды насилия, которые оставляют синяки в душе на долгие годы. 
но реальность такова, что психологическое насилие влияет на психику человека так-же пагубно, как и физическое. только синяки никто не увидит. а они есть, и они болят. 
но вся “соль” в другом. психологическое насилие - это яд, который отравляет жизнь жертвы незаметно. как в той притче про лягушку, где ей постепенно подогревали воду, и в итоге она сварилась. и это - страшно. потому что жертва сама не замечает, как только вчера проверяли ее телефон, а сегодня уже избивают. страшно то, что где психологическое насилие сегодня - там будет физическое завтра. 
вопрос времени и социальных связей. абьюзер делает все, чтобы у жертвы осталось как можно меньше социальных связей, чтобы ей банально было не к кому обратиться за помощью тогда, когда, а не если насилие будет физическим. 
поэтому насилие - это априори плохо. любое. 
насилие не может быть необходимостью. 
не может быть необходимостью попытка уничтожить личность другого человека. 
я пишу об этом, потому что это важно. 
потому что #16днівпротинасильства.
потому что #япротинасильства, и потому что если бы я знала об этом раньше - два года своей жизни я бы прожила по-другому. 
если бы это знали мои родители - я бы знала, что это не ок, когда какой-то парень пытается рассказывать мне, во сколько я буду возвращаться домой, и юбки какой длинны я буду носить. 
если бы это знали мои подруги - они бы знали, какими словами донести мне, что настоящая любовь - совсем другая.
#психологкакстильжизни
.
.
.
#hearmetoo

text:
me resulta aterrador el punto al que estamos llegando en nuestro país.
•
creo que hay demasiada gente que vive desde el odio, y también creo que hay mucha gente inconsciente que cuando quiera darse cuenta de lo que ha votado, ya será demasiado tarde.
•
me parece intolerable que se permita la existencia de partidos, asociaciones o cualquier tipo de entidad fascista. pero seguimos anclados.
•
aún así, este es el momento para estar más fuertes que nunca, para luchar con más ganas de las que jamás hayamos mostrado, mantenernos firmes y defendiendo nuestra posición y nuestros derechos.
•
no nos rindamos, terminaremos ganando. estoy segura.

text:
join us for a festive late opening tonight, 18.00-20.00 @ morley gallery.

women’s work highlights historic, modern and contemporary work by women in the southwark’s art collection.
2018 has been an important year for raising issues about women’s equality and recognition. there are many powerful stories, from the centenary of women’s partial suffrage in 1918 to the #metoo movement. this exhibition makes visible a selection of female artists and raises questions about the structures that impact the ways in which women artists are represented, displayed and collected.

featured artists include margaret sarah carpenter, prunella clough, anya gallaccio, grace golden, barbara hepworth, sarah lucas, saskia olde wolbers and bertha newcombe.

image credit: southwark shop front - grace golden

text:
are you beautiful? 
beauty is everywhere, in us and around us everyday you just have to see it with your heart and your minds eye.

there were many years when i question this for myself, are you beautiful not just my external outer shell but my internal inner shell.

then i discovered the true essesence of self love and understanding that i have to love myself truly before i can see the beauty that i hold as a person, which has been a journey. 
i no longer care about what people think of me and how they judge me because i know i come from a place of love and have so much to give to the universe and the people that i connect with are the ones that are meant to be in my life so i can give to them and them to me.

so when i look at the phase you are beautiful, i truly believe i am and all of you are as beauty is what our essence is made of. 
don't allow others to say any different and effect your way of thinking as you were put in the universe to share your essence and write your own story.

yes you are beautiful

text: reflection (movements): in the last decade several ads and social movements have sprung up to bring awareness to sexual assault including #thatsharassment, #metoo, the truth has a voice, and time’s up (zost, 2018). these operations not only aid in the promotion of sexual assault education and dispelling stigma, but they also help to encourage survivors who have yet to seek help know that they are not alone. this is the heart of the #metoo movement, which aims to give survivors a voice. this mirror reflects the twinship that survivors find in these movements with people who have gone through similar experiences as them. the mirror shows rays of light, crossing paths and shining across each other. these are the hopeful connections that take place when two or more survivors have the opportunity to meet and find solace in the sharing of one another’s stories. local events that take place at texas a&m university san antonio include a block party to help students foster community and provide a safer alternative to partying, programming such as active bystander intervention training, national night out to bring awareness to who is in the community to support individuals, and a peaceful protest on campus against kavanaugh that took place this semester (k. frank, personal communication, october 4, 2018; r. lutz-guevara, personal communication, october 5, 2018).

text:
a couple friends and i were talking about how ridiculous it was to ban “baby it’s cold outside” for the alleged ‘rape’ content in the christmas classic. this lead to an insightful discussion into the modern trends of ‘acceptable’ versus ‘unacceptable’ language and ideas and how it should be approached and navigated in a classroom. 
we came to the general consensus that minors should not be held accountable for their communication of language and idea(l)s no matter how “problematic” or at odds with our own beliefs. instead as educators, we should serve to expose and equip students with critical thought, analysis, and healthy doses of opposition so that students may organically arrive at their own conclusions in a way that fits with their personal beliefs, identities, and experiences. we suggested that a good way to approach this may be to ask the student to write a text explaining, arguing, and justifying their belief as an assessment to show that they posses these skills even if they do not agree with the content or ideas we perpetuate through exploring a topic.
this meme is a satirical list of christmas songs that are “problematic”
what are your thoughts?

text:
#metoo stings karnataka bjp leaders as young bbmp councillor breaks silence

bengaluru, dec 6: netra pallavi m, a bharatiya janata party councilor of bruhat bengaluru mahanagara palike (bbmp) has levelled allegations of sexual harassment against her own party’s leadership.

33-year-old pallavi, who represents atturu ward in bbmp on wednesday told media persons that a few senior bjp leaders sought ‘favours’ from certain woman councillors.

the bjp leadership, however, denied her allegations and warned her of disciplinary action if he continues to level allegation against her own party.

pallavi was unavailable for comment after her statements were aired, and her phone remained switched off.

text:
this time of year makes me anxious and overall, easily triggered. although i'm proud of my physical weight loss journey, this is also an improvement on my mental health as well. this dress in particular honestly holds triggers in a way. 
the last time i wore this outfit, i was walking out of the hospital new year's day, puzzled and scared. i couldn't think straight. any form of trust i had towards those around me was shut down. being sexually assaulted by a "friend" next to my friend was never my intentions that night. the whole situation truly dulled my personal confidence and really made me not want to live. another scar on my body of dark secrets..but refuse to keep secrets like this anymore.

it has not been an easy 2ish years but something tells me my journey isn't over with those in my life and this new chapter with my new shield of armor. ❤️ each year i'm growing, even if i fall in between. .
.
.
#weightlossjourney #mentalhealth #improvement #respectwomen #nomeansno #strongwilled #womanempowerment #metoo #staystrong

text:
last night i launched shenetworks in london at wework, soho. it was my dream to take shenetworks to a bigger platform, to give my local community opportunities across the uk to collaborate and make things happen.

last night was proof to me that networking and collaboration is key to our success. the greatest gift we can give each other, is each other. the strength in the room tonight was exactly why we came into london. to be with women who want to make a difference to all of our lives, women who know the importance of working alongside each other.

our speakers jay diamond, shola kaye and susan kabani were beautifully focused on empowering women. i was proud to share the stage with them all.

the most talented and amazing anna caterina-florio hosted tonight’s first event. she’s a real force of everything that shenetworks stands for and was a delight to us all the entire evening, thank you anna. it’s always a pleasure to see you 💖 
thank you also must go to the shenetworks london partner ugenie for bringing such strength of community to our lives. such an honour to work alongside you.

i want to give back, support others, give you your voice back and discover new opportunities.

someone wrote in my secret santa christmas card today “nothing can dim your light”. it’s true, nothing can. 
happy days 🙏🏼 @susiekabani @sholakaye @ladyjaydiamond www.emmajanetaylor.life

text:
kadına yönelik şiddetle mücadele kampanyası kapsamında, msyd-asra olarak başlattığımız 16 günlük aktivizm programlarımız devam ediyor. #orangetheworld #hearmetoo hareketi altında mülteci kadınlarla biraraya gelerek bu özel günü konuştuk. bu günün önemine dikkat çekerek onlardan tüm dünyaya kendi dileklerini anlattıkları bir mektup yazmalarını istedik.

our 16-day activism programs, which we started as msyd-asra, continue in the context of the november 25th day against violence against women. with #orangetheworld #hearmetoo movement”
we met with refugee women and talked about this special day. drawing attention to the importance of this day, we asked them to write a letter to the whole world telling their own wishes.

برامج النشطة لمدة 16 يومًا ،ابتداءا من يوم 25 نوفمبر
التي بدأناها نحن كمنظمة msyd-asra ، تستمر في سياق العنف ضد المرأة. مع "حركة أورانج في العالم #hearmetoo
التقينا باللاجئات وتحدثنا عن هذا اليوم الخاص. لفتنا الانتباه إلى أهمية هذا اليوم ، وطلبنا منهم كتابة رسالة إلى العالم كله تحكي رغباتهم الخاصة

text:
"when you’ve been through some of the things that i’ve been through and you try to voice your opinions, people don’t get it. people don’t understand why you believe the things you do. people believe what they’ve believed their whole lives and they don’t want to believe anything else. my mom had to take me to planned parenthood to make sure i didn’t have any form of stds or anything like that. i had to keep going to the doctors every week to keep getting tested for pregnancy just in case. there was absolutely no birth control used. there were a few times that he made me take plan b. but not every time. so when people talk about wanting to ban abortion and people are like, “don’t have sex,” that’s not it. girls aren’t just going off and not being safe. there are times when things happen like that. but girls like me that have been through all of this stuff and they need that there. it really bothers me. when you try to voice that opinion people don’t listen to you. especially when you’re a tiny little white girl. people think i don’t know what i’m talking about. they think i’m trying to fit in with the media and fit in with everyone else by believing a certain way. but people don’t think about what people have been through that makes them believe a certain way. and it’s on both sides. but after everything that i’ve been through it’s hard to try to make people believe things. even when people talk about, “oh she was probably raped for the way that she dresses.” but people don’t think about children. i was very little. i was a little emo kid with bands shirts, jeans, and converse. that was me growing up. there was nothing to provoke that, i was just being a kid. people don’t get that sometimes." -aly
-----

text:
"it was so much for everyone. no one knew what to do. that was it. after fighting it for a year and everything we went through, it just wasn’t heard. people just didn’t listen. none of us knew what to do. we had to sit there and be like, “that was that. we have to move on.” there’s no point in fighting it. we were shown that no one was on our side. we aren’t going to keep trying to fight for people to be on our side. i think that’s why people are so scared to come out with it. they’re going to try to fight it and no one is going to be on their side. and then they’ll just feel worse than they already do about everything. and it just scares people. it was horrible to hear from a judge. especially from a woman. especially from a woman with kids. to listen to a mother and daughter explain all of the things that they went through and just not believe them. it was horrible to see. even my mom brought up things to me that she went through that i had no idea about that happened between them. it was horrible to hear that she wasn’t believed. we put everything we had, even my money for college, in this case. and everything just all at once was over. after an entire year. he’s allowed to find another job. he’s allowed to do whatever. but i won’t ever get my childhood back. i’m not going to get back the life that i missed out on." -aly -----

text:
"when i was about three or four my mom met my stepdad. after a month they got married. he took me in. from the ages of four to about 16 or 17 he sexually abused me. for 12 years. my mother didn’t know. my grandparents didn’t know. it was just me keeping it to myself for 12 years. they got divorced when i was in seventh grade. i would switch back and forth between their houses. when it was just him and me i wouldn’t sleep. i had really bad insomnia. i would get about two hours of sleep a week. school was very difficult. when i got off the bus when he would pick me up from my stop i wouldn’t talk to anyone. i would just rush to the car so he wouldn’t ask questions or anything. when i would take a shower i would turn my phone on silent in case anyone texted me. i would turn my phone on airplane mode at night so no one would text me throughout the night. if i would get random wrong number calls it would just be accusations for hours on end. hours and hours. sometimes until like four in the morning. i would try to go to bed and then have to wake up at 5 to go to school. it was extremely rough as a child. i wasn’t allowed to have friends. my gay best friend was the only guy i was ever allowed to be friends with. if i was even in a school project with a boy i would get yelled at. if i wasn’t allowed to pick my group and there was a boy in my group i would have to give my stepdad proof or have my teacher send him something to show that i had to do it for school and it was mandatory." -aly
-----

text:
my wcw everyday 😍💕 malala yousafzai 😍 pakistani human rights activist and the youngest nobel prize laureate. especially known for female education advocacy in pakistan where girls are banned from attending school.👑 in 2012 she was shot in an assassination attempt in retaliation for her activism. following her recovery, she became a prominent activist for the right to education and founded the malala fund.💪 her advocacy has grown into an international movement and has resulted in the international denouncing of the taliban. 🙅

muslim girls from islamic states seldomly have access to or even the right to education but because of girls like malala many muslim girls around the world now know that banning girls from education has no place in islam.💕👑 #istandwithmalala 👊 📷 @malalafund

text:
is the workplace more stressful than it was? do employees feel more under pressure than before? are staff feeling burdened by work emails around the clock? recent data and surveys suggest there is an increasing problem writes hugh pym.

now one business owner wants other employers to follow his lead and allow employees to do a four-day week and to switch off completely on the fifth day.

ankur shah runs lifestyle brands company mahabis and says he lets staff, within reason, choose where they work on the four days as long as they are in contact via email or skype.

there is also no monitoring of working hours. #youwillbearwitness #emdr #erinfado #therapydog #metoo #ptsd #peterfox #ptsdsurvivor #ptsdrecovery #ptsdawareness #stopracism #stopbullying #stopchildabuse #dissociativeidentitydisorder #cardinalpell

california national organization for women is hosting the annual gender equity awards on december 8, 2018 at 5pm. at the the mayme a. clayton library and museum in culver city.  we have #americanhorrorstory fan favorite @naomiwgrossman  serving as our mc and a special appearance by runway coach and tv personality @missjalexander. 
join us as we celebrate community & business leaders, senior executives, and activist who have made a remarkable contribution to championing gender balance and equality of opportunity in their organizations.

click on the button below for tickets and i hope to see you there!

text:
5 things to know about maya angelou’s complicated, meaningful life

it’s only fitting that the first week of u.s. national poetry month in april coincides with what would have been the 90th birthday of the poet maya angelou, who died may 28, 2014, at the age of 86.
 but while she’s best known today for her writing — as the author of more than 30 books and the recipient of more than 50 honorary degrees — she had many different careers before becoming a writer, and all before the age of 40, as time pointed out in her  2014 obituary . such jobs included: cook, waitress, sex-worker, dancer, actor, playwright, editor at an english-language newspaper in egypt, calypso singer ,  and cast member of the opera  porgy and bess.  in fact, h er name is more of a stage name than a pen name; she was born marguerite annie johnson in st. louis in 1928, but in the 1950s came up with “maya angelou,” which is a  portmanteau  of sorts, by combining her childhood nickname and a riff on her then-husband’s surname.  in a  google  doodle marking her april 4 birthday, she can be heard reading “  still  i rise , ” alongside testimonials from her son  guy johnson, oprah winfrey, laverne cox, alicia keys, america ferrera, and martina mcbride. the 15-time grammy-winner keys calls her a “renaissance woman,” while 14-time grammy nominee mcbride says angelou inspired her to write her own songs. winfrey, who has called angelou  a mentor , says that “maya angelou is not what she has  done or written or spoken, it’s how she did it all. she moved through the world with unshakeable calm, confidence, and a fiery, fierce grace and abounding love.” here are five things to know about the literary legend:  i know why the caged bird sings  was her first book
 as the world marks her birthday in 2018, maya angelou’s breakout work is particularly relevant to the national conversation. long before the #metoo and #timesup movements brought sexual assault into the national conversation, she wrote in her 1969 memoir about her own experience with sexual trauma, and how her mother’s boyfriend raped her when she was a child. he was convicted and imprisoned, and after his release he was be

💬 foi uma das primeiras a apoiar o #metoo. onde está a indústria neste momento?
💬 dakota: eu apoio o time's up e #metoo cem por cento. mas eu acho que, como resultado, todo mundo mantém sua guarda alta em hollywood. não há mais calor nesta indústria. mesmo assim, tudo tem sido muito positivo para as mulheres e para a igualdade de gênero no ambiente de trabalho. eu acho que é importante para o progresso do desenvolvimento humano. é um momento tão interessante quanto peculiar e estou muito grata por haver tantas mulheres incrivelmente inteligentes nessa indústria que estão levando isso adiante para o benefício de todo o mundo. de qualquer forma, eu geralmente fico tão chocada com o que está acontecendo no mundo que pensar sobre os problemas de hollywood não está entre minhas prioridades. — entrevista para o site la vanguardia, dezembro 2018 ♡

text:
“what good do your words do if they can’t understand you? don’t go talking that shit....” | the mother edition @erykahbadu⁣
⁣
🌱⁣
⁣
i took a spiritual journey through her art and it genuinely redefined my heart. i learned the feeling of love from multiple perspectives and felt the frequency of love in the highest degrees. ⁣
⁣
🌱⁣
⁣
i found that love was intelligence. something that needed to be studied before it was felt. a certain responsibility comes with feeling something so deeply. one that can only be understood with emotional maturity. ⁣
⁣
🌱⁣
⁣
love can’t be defined by feelings; it can only be measured through them. the definition of love can only be expressed through connection. two important components: compatibility and adaptability. how deeply can you understand your partner? how well can you respond to your partner’s evolution? love is when your emotions learn to speak the same language. when hearts learn to have healthy communication with one another. ⁣
⁣
🌱⁣

text:
quando começamos a ficar irritados em relação ao outro, isso geralmente é acionado por causa de como estamos absorvendo o comportamento do outro.é bom lembrar de como é difícil mudar a nós mesmos e ao nosso comportamento.

quando nossa própria felicidade depende de outra pessoa estamos entrando numa viagem infeliz.  isso significa que estamos colocando nossa felicidade fora do nosso controle. o problema é que as pessoas não mudam porque queremos que elas mudem. em última análise, eles mudam - ou não - porque elas querem.

pense na grande mudança que enfrentou com você mesmo, o quanto é e foi difīcil. quando lembrar você estará controlando você. a mudança pode ser difícil o suficiente para integrarmos a nós mesmos.

pessoas felizes sabem que é inútil tentar mudar outras pessoas, pois o melhor é a mudança de ser e ter o controle de si. 
podemos através de atitudes inspirar outras, mas nunca forçarmos a uma mudança. 
#mulher

quando nossa própria felicidade depende de outra pessoa estamos entrando numa viagem infeliz.  isso significa que estamos colocando nossa felicidade fora do nosso controle. o problema é que as pessoas não mudam porque queremos que elas mudem. em última análise, eles mudam - ou não - porque elas querem.

pense na grande mudança que enfrentou com você mesmo, o quanto é e foi difīcil. quando lembrar você estará controlando você. a mudança pode ser difícil o suficiente para integrarmos a nós mesmos.

pessoas felizes sabem que é inútil tentar mudar outras pessoas, pois o melhor é a mudança de ser e ter o controle de si. 
podemos através de atitudes inspirar outras, mas nunca forçarmos a uma mudança.

text:
дамы, если вы такие же модницы как я, и следите за новыми трендами, имеете собственный стиль, то эта статья придется вам по душе.
выбрала для вас 10 модных трендов сезона осень-зима 2018/2019
что ж, поехали, красотки 👠

ключевые тренды осени сложны и самодостаточны. их можно носить как самостоятельно, так и смешивать между собой в любых пропорциях. главное - мода наступающего сезона уважает небанальные сочетания и измененные пропорции тела.

этой осенью никуда не скрыться от обилия анималистических принтов. живописные пятна шкур леопарда, оцелота, зебры и тигра густо покрыли подиумы четырех главных модных столиц мира. 
начавшаяся несколько сезонов назад лихорадка под названием "логомания" в новом сезоне сбавлять оборотов не собирается. не остались к ней равнодушны наступающей осенью даже такие стойкие к массовым тенденциям бренды как max mara и prada.

с любовью ваш стилист ♥️листайте ниже👇🏻

text:
menurut catatan tahunan komnas perempuan di tahun 2017, dari 350.000 kasus kekerasan terhadap perempuan yang tercatat, 20% diantaranya terjadi di ruang publik. sementara sisanya yang terbesar adalah dalam hubungan pribadi dan keluarga. bahkan dalam dunia maya dan teknologi komunikasi, kekerasan seksual terjadi.
korban masih saja disalahkan, aparat hukum pun melakukan viktimisasi sementara pelaku bebas berkeliaran. belum adanya aturan khusus tentang kekerasan seksual membuat pencegahan dan penanganan kekerasan seksual terhambat.
namun begitu sudah ada ruu penghapusan kekerasan seksual yang direncanakan menjadi payung hukum masih belum disahkan hingga kini.
yuk kita kumpul bersama untuk mendorong pengesahan ruupks.

text:
i want to be able to share stories, but also discuss upon real societal issues through poetry.

text:
this damn song 🎶

i write songs about a lot of things, from deeply personal experiences that end up writing themselves into a song to numerous experiences combined to create one overall, somewhat cryptic song. this song is about many experiences and ideas flowing through my head, and today it represented my struggle with #selflove . with years of emotional abuse from relationships, and coping with an assault, i’ve found myself thinking i’ve hit rock bottom. but recently, i’ve felt nothing but moving up, slowly, but surely. i am reclaiming my power, redefining my voice, and using my pain to make beautiful music. and for that, i am grateful. #phillylocalmusic #singersongwriter #originalmusic #phillymusicscene #songwriter #metoo #loveyourself #newmusic #phillysingers #newalbum #newsong #phl

text:
read this: superstition? hijo de puta / son of a bitch. my mother has broken two bonds associated/related to the mother of my child. trying to understand ? unfortunately fortunately one of the reasons i can understand and/or feel comfortable around pure hatred is because i know my mother. and/or superstitious? i guess you could believe there’s logical reasons to you why my mother would do that. i know facts are my mother likely knows how to obtain a bail bond without issue. i also know that there were issues with why that bind was requested or needed so .... logical ? i could imagine my mother having such hatred for anyone fucking with me or her granddaughter that every single thing she did bonded you. realistically i’ve never heard of a bail bonds issue (twice) as happened to me although ... unfortunately i had previously heard of people getting falsely arrested on made up charges, the usual suspects or just the usual either way look into that and ... and well they’re related so if you think my mother fucked up or did the right thing it’s likely either way your bind is what she wanted. 🤔 awww, can’t say we’ve never bonded though, although it’s also true there’s been times i didn’t ask or even want it from her. facts like that. whether you think it’s all some sort of blah blah whatever or not facts are while it may seem like my mother has acted against me in each step she has both spiritually and legally bound every single person that had acted against me to pay (fuck you, pay ...) at some point and if you “think” she’s willing to put me through some horrible horrible binds/situations/issues/life i don’t think you could imagine what she would do to you.
.
so... it feels odd to just say i’ve used some techiniques/prayers/spirituality similarly to how it’s been said was used in what is now called haiti without also acknowledging as taught/seen/inherited from my mother. personally i think she maybe bipolar. why has that been difficult to address you ask as she’d say you’re an idiot. because you can somehow believe that my mother would truly go against me. #metoo though , i could believe that too if it wasn’t for what i know ... oh you know my mother? (continues )

text:
i’m beyond grateful; my book the namaste way has been accepted for publication by inanna publications.
.
i did not start writing until i was in my mid fifty. 
i never knew there was a writer in me waiting to come out.
now two of my books are going to be published;
🌟never without love 🌟the namaste way
.
i’m touched...humbled...in love ❤️ .
the namaste way is a collection of short stories that takes the readers deep into the heartbreak and loss of identity suffered by the protagonist of each story, the situation many women find themselves in when they fall. 
readers ascend towards the light once the protagonists break out of the shells that have been imprisoning them and set out in search of finding their own inner pearls. .
namaste
the light within me honours the light within you
.
my soul sister, my rock, and my editor cathryn matthes thank you!!
my amazing editor nina shoroplova, thank you 🙏🏼

text: it’s been a busy time of year for #cfawl members! we supported our pr director lauren millcarek at the @fba_orlando new members reception. we partnered with @ocbayls to put on a #metoo cle. cfawl members also attended yls’s great luncheon featuring john morgan. we applauded cfawl member judge-elect amy carter as she received famu law’s distinguished alumni award. we attended sfawl’s first event as a new #fawl chapter. and we supported cfawl member annie kwong at the holiday party for the greater orlando asian-american bar association. phew! it’s that time of year 🥳 congratulations all on these great events - can’t wait to see you all at our own holiday party lunch on friday! 🎄 #cfawlconnects #orlvba #vba #fbaorlando #ocbayls #goaaba

text:
baby gates! 
babies! and dogs!  have a safe place for the dog to be where it doesn't need to worry about being disturbed. gate off the kitchen or laundry room, or master bedroom. dog can count on baby-free floor space and uninterrupted sleep. parents can count on no bites to the face or muzzle punches. crawling babies and toddlers are at risk for a while, and fearful dogs need protection from crossing the line. i much prefer careful management rather than relying on training when the risks are gigantic. we love having an extended gate that opens with one hand and allows us to have the dogs in part of the kitchen, near the action, but separated from toddler unless directly closely supervised.
🐕🐶👼

text:
look out! it's the #funpolice coming to ruin christmas songs & children's shows near you!  #tinatoon #wednesdaywisdom #charliebrownthanksgiving #rudolphtherednosedreindeer #babyitscoldoutside 
look out! it’s the left’s fun police!  in the #metoo era, any remote suggestion of men “taking advantage” of innocent young women must be wiped away from history. “baby, its cold outside,” a classic christmas song for over 50 years, must be banned from the airwaves! it doesn’t matter that 94% of the radio stations listeners said no to the ban, the radio station caved to the 6% that voted the christmas song is inappropriate. outraged feminists that make up 6% can dictate to the majority what they can and cannot listen to at christmas?

it is a cold and lonely christmas when the #metooers are huddled near the space heater with their six cats, drinking wine and eating that pizza for one as the resentment against men festers inside them. if they can’t have fun, then no one deserves to have fun.

stop in the name of the fun police! rudolph you are “problematic”, the fun police pronounced about “rudolph, the red-nosed reindeer” the favorite christmas show of millions of children around the world. seems rudolph’s dad was bullying him and donner was a racist bigot against “red-nosed” reindeer. presumably this fell in the same category as atrocities committed against native americans. who knew?

no justice! no charlie brown thanksgiving! charlie brown and the whole gang (including that bigot snoopy) were accused of bigotry and racism against the only black child in the “hood” when he was seated across from the gang. the fun police claimed this was blatant racism when actually he got the best seat in the house. where’s black lives matter when you need them?

how dare you! you are not inclusive! the fun police charged the “victoria secret” show featuring beautiful women dressed as angels in skimpy outfits. where are the trans gender women? where are the lesbians? where are the plus, plus size models? they need representation too!

text:
i will say it again, and again... and again
📢
no one ever has the right to put their hands on you, if you don't want them to. 📢
it doesn't matter what you are wearing
it doesn't matter what your relationship to them is
📢
it doesn't matter how long you have known them
📢
it doesn't matter if it wasn't 'really' a big deal
📢
it doesn't matter what you said or did
📢
it doesn't matter if you welcomed it before
📢
if you don't consent to someone putting their hands on any part of your body, they do not have the right to do it
📢
speak out, speak up and act. 📢
support others who need their voice to be heard. 
we need to come together, to take responsibility before something happens, and to find better ways to respond. teaching confidence, assertiveness, courage, and self-defense is not the whole answer. 📢
i will say it again and again, and i will act to keep making ripples of change. ————————————

really struggling today and tonight as i’ve been thinking about a polygamy criminal case that will be in the courts tomorrow.... i have soo many thoughts and i cannot even put them together!!! a woman was beat by her husband, she fled the aub polygamous group with her children, husband bails himself out, threatens her on a recorded phone call to drop charges, case takes 2 years to go to trial, utah’s previous attorney general mark shurtleff (who was charged with accepting bribes and such) is the attorney for the polygamist husband, and now the state of utah is planning to plea down the charges without even taking the case to trial ..... did i miss something or does so much make sense now? 
recap.... previous attorney general for the state of utah is a lawyer defending a polygamist man who beat his wife... no wonder systemic polygamy has flourished so well in the state of utah, no wonder criminal behavior in polygamy has been ignored, no wonder it has been an uphill battle to get authorities to do something/anything to protect the victims of systemic polygamy.... no wonder.... #escapingpolygamy #nationalnews #utahnews #utahpolitics #utpol @cnnpolitics @cnn @andersoncooper #domesticviolence #domesticviolenceawareness @domesticviolence #polygamynews @bbcnews @abcworldnewstonight @metoomvmt #metoo #metoomovement #humanrights #feminism #womensrights #sharegoodness

text:
we can do hard things.
.
like speak to our church about women’s equality, rights, trafficking, sexual assault and how we vote affects women not only in the states, but globally.
.
the truth is, we can’t help women overseas until we change the way we treat women in our own culture, that includes the church.
.
i might catch some heat for it later, but for now i’m proud of using the voice god gave me.
.
we can do hard things, friends. don’t be afraid to use your voice.
.
also, dress because #dressember day five.
.
#faithandfeminism #jesusfeminist #equality #timesup #metoo #useyourvoice

text:
health-care professionals
know the signs that indicate a person may be experiencing gender based violence...
*frequent appointments for vague symptoms
*injuries inconsistent with explanation of cause
*woman tries to hide injuries or minimize their extent
**partner always attends unnecessarily
*woman is reluctant to speak in front of partner
*non-compliance with treatment
*frequently missed appointments
*multiple injuries at different stages of healing
*patient appears frightened, overly anxious or depressed
*woman is submissive or afraid to speak in front of her partner
*partner is aggressive or dominant, talks for the woman or refuses to leave the room
*poor or non-attendance at antenatal clinics
*early self-discharge from hospital

text:
i’ve tried my hardest to bite my tongue. i can’t... i just can’t. 
and why should i bite my tongue? 
i’ve already shared my story, here and on my blog. it has no power over me. i am a survivor. not a victim. 
the song “baby it’s cold outside” has been one of my very most favourite christmas songs since i was a little girl. 
it still is. i belt that song out, word for word, all christmas season long. in fact, i sing it allllll the time. 
it. is. not. “a little rapey” 
nothing about this song “triggers” me. reminds me. scares me. 
banning it from radio?! this bull has got to stop. 
this song has been around forever. 
it carries many warm fuzzies for me, as i’m sure many others as well. 
come on. what is this world coming to? 
that’s what scares me.

text:
@maddowshow @nyt.fi @huffpost i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the bombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on my bed.

the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still, today, right now.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are just helpless with the fake content - there is no way they are going to risk their business by taking a real responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

and here comes the best part. trumq is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words.

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
"it was september of last year when i was in an almost-empty bus, heading home. i chose to sit in the farthest sear. not too long after i got in, a group of five men got in and scattered themselves across the bus. the youngest of them, who seemed to be around my age, sat across from the long rear seat of the bus next to me. the other four had the audacity to turn all the way around to face me and stare shamelessly with smug looks on their faces. no words were said - just the incessant stare directed at me by all five of them was enough to make me feel defenseless, nervous and angry. i've never had the courage to speak up, but i stared directly at the boy next to me. i wondered what would happen if i stared back. he had no dignity to look away. in fact, staring back seemed to excite them even more. i went on to ask him, "ඇයි ඔහොම බලන් ඉන්නෙ? කෙල්ලෙක් දැකලා නැද්ද මීට කලින්? ("why are you looking at me like that? have you never seen a girl before?"). this made them look at me in surprise. i guess they did not expect a girl to confront them. just as i said this, the boy i spoke to got off the bus immediately. the rest followed" - renushi
.

if you witness sexual harassment in public transport: intervene. speak up. be the change.

tweet_full:
"it was september of last year when i was in an almost-empty bus, heading home. i chose to sit in the farthest sear. not too long after i got in, a group of five men got in and scattered themselves across the bus. the youngest of them, who seemed to be around my age, sat across from the long rear seat of the bus next to me. the other four had the audacity to turn all the way around to face me and stare shamelessly with smug looks on their faces. no words were said - just the incessant stare directed at me by all five of them was enough to make me feel defenseless, nervous and angry. i have never had the courage to speak up, but i stared directly at the boy next to me. i wondered what would happen if i stared back. he had no dignity to look away. in fact, staring back seemed to excite them even more. i went on to ask him, "ඇයි ඔහොම බලන් ඉන්නෙ? කෙල්ලෙක් දැකලා නැද්ද මීට කලින්? ("why are you looking at me like that? have you never seen a girl before?"). this made them look at me in surprise. i guess they did not expect a girl to confront them. just as i said this, the boy i spoke to got off the bus immediately. the rest followed" - renushi
.

text:
on wednesdays, we read 📚
while searching through a bookcase full of 90s self help books, academic writings, and classic novels, i came across this book. forgiveness has always been a challenge for me, so it was interesting to gather a new perspective on what it means to “forgive the monsters” in our lives. key takeaways:
🌱 the monsters in our head are people. by humanizing them, we are bringing them back down to an attainable level of humanity that is forgivable.
🌱 on forgiving your god: we focus so much on what god didn’t do that we let the countless good days slip from memory. 🌱 forgiveness is like a muscle. the more you practice it, the more it builds, and the more you can exercise it in your favor

text:
@maddowshow @nyt.fi @huffpost i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the bombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on my bed.

the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still, today, right now.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are just helpless with the fake content - there is no way they are going to risk their business by taking a real responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

and here comes the best part. trumq is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words.

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

a non

text:
yesterday, forbes published the world's 100 most powerful women list, but a look back at 2018 proves that you don’t need a prestigious title or a seven-figure salary to change the world for women. meet the "other power women": 1. jodi kantor and megan twohey, who published an investigation revealing decades of sexual harassment and rape allegations against hollywood executive harvey weinstein. 
2.  the usa gymnastics team who brought to justice usa gymnastics (usag) and michigan state university trainer larry nassar. 
3.  the women of the google walkout who demanded changes to the toxic workplace culture. 
and many more who raised their voices to protect and empower other women.  #powerwomen #futureisfemale #womenleaders #change #googlewalkout #metoo #genderequality 
source: forbes

text:
look out! it's the #funpolice coming to ruin christmas songs & children's shows near you! 
look out! it’s the left’s fun police! 
in the #metoo era, any remote suggestion of men “taking advantage” of innocent young women must be wiped away from history. “baby, its cold outside,” a classic christmas song for over 50 years, must be banned from the airwaves! it doesn’t matter that 94% of the radio stations listeners said no to the ban, the radio station caved to the 6% that voted the christmas song is inappropriate. outraged feminists that make up 6% can dictate to the majority what they can and cannot listen to at christmas?

it is a cold and lonely christmas when the #metooers are huddled near the space heater with their six cats, drinking wine and eating that pizza for one as the resentment against men festers inside them. if they can’t have fun, then no one deserves to have fun.

stop in the name of the fun police! rudolph you are “problematic”, the fun police pronounced about “rudolph, the red-nosed reindeer” the favorite christmas show of millions of children around the world. seems rudolph’s dad was bullying him and donner was a racist bigot against “red-nosed” reindeer. presumably this fell in the same category as atrocities committed against native americans. who knew?

no justice! no charlie brown thanksgiving! charlie brown and the whole gang (including that bigot snoopy) were accused of bigotry and racism against the only black child in the “hood” when he was seated across from the gang. the fun police claimed this was blatant racism when actually he got the best seat in the house. where’s black lives matter when you need them?

how dare you! you are not inclusive! the fun police charged the “victoria secret” show featuring beautiful women dressed as angels in skimpy outfits. where are the trans gender women? where are the lesbians? where are the plus, plus size models? they need representation too!

it comes down to this. will you continue to let a small minority of nagging scolds ruin your holidays and relationships? who made them the moral authority in this country and why do companies listen to them and cave in? because they are loud and persistent
name: Peter Salomone

text:
every year, we invite survivors of domestic violence and sexual assault to visit our holiday gift store. they are able to shop for their family members and themselves. although they get to shop for their gifts, all of the gifts are free! we are only able to do this because of the care and support we receive from our communities.

if you are unable to donate, please support us by spreading the word!! suggested items to donate:
non gender specific gifts for adults: new scarves, hats, gloves, socks, bath/shaving sets. small household items: new toasters, blenders, dish sets, blankets. gifts for teens: gift cards, nail polish sets, cosmetics, head phones.

thank you community for all you do to support survivors!!! for more information about where to drop off donations, please contact:  ldegaray@elprograma.org

cada año, invitamos a sobrevivientes de asalto sexual y violencia domestica a visitar nuestra tienda de regalos. ¡los sobrevivientes compran no solo para sus seres queridos sino también para ellos mismos! aunque ell@s escojen los regalos, todos los regalos some gratis.

su apoyo es fundamental para garantizar que podamos continuar nuestra misión colectiva para empoderar y apoyar a nuestras familias y comunidades.

no importa que tan grande o pequeña sea su contribución, incluso el simple hecho de compartir esta información, su acto de bondad tocará los corazones de los demás de maneras increíbles. 
los artículos más necesarios incluyen:
regalos no específicos de género para adultos tales como: nuevas bufandas, sombreros, guantes, juegos de baño/para afeitar, calcetines. artículos para el hogar como: nuevas tostadoras, licuadoras, vajillas, cobijas. regalos para adolescentes como: tarjetas de regalo, sets de esmalte de uñas, cosméticos, audífonos 
gracias a la comunidad por todo lo que hacen para apoyar a los sobrevivientes!

para más información contacte a: ldegaray@elprograma.org #supportsurvivors #latinx #survivors #community #proyectounica #projectunica #metoo

text:
@arimelber @donlemoncnn @seanhannity @maddowshow @thejimmydoreshow @cnn @nbcnews wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates suppoed by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

cu devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

time to stir that congress cauldron.... alexandria ocasio-cortez- born october 13, 1989, in #newyorkcity, ocasio-cortez worked as lead educational strategist at gageis, inc. and was an educator at the nonprofit national hispanic institute. she is the member-elect of the u.s. house of representatives for new york's 14th congressional district and will be the youngest woman to serve in congress in #unitedstates history.

ayanna s. pressley- born february 3, 1974 in #chicago, illinois, pressley was the first black woman elected to the boston city council where she currently serves as an at-large member and is the first black woman elected to congress from #massachusetts as member-elect of the u.s. house of representatives, serving massachusetts's 7th congressional district.

ilhan omar- born october 4, 1981 in mogadishu, #somalia, omar is the director of policy & initiatives of the women organizing women network and is the first somali american elected to legislative office in the united states where she is the member-elect of the u.s. house of representatives for #minnesota's 5th congressional district.

debra a. haaland- born december 2, 1960, in winslow, #arizona, haaland is part #nativeamerican and member of the #lagunapueblo people. she is a former chair of the democratic party of #newmexico and the member-elect of the u.s. house of representatives for new mexico's 1st congressional district.

veronica escobar- born september 15, 1969 in el paso, #texas, escobar served as a county commissioner and county judge for #elpaso county from 2010 to 2017 and is the member-elect of the u.s. house of representatives for texas's 16th congressional district.

sharice davids- born may 22, 1980 in #frankfurt, west germany, davids is native american and a member of the #hochunk nation. she is an attorney and the member-elect of the u.s. house of representatives for #kansas's 3rd congressional district.

text:
since you decided to pull “baby it’s cold outside” from its playlist because someone was offended, i feel that these other holiday songs are also on the chopping block. 
how did our generation ever survive?

1. i saw mommy kissing santa claus: subjecting minors to softcore porn

2. the christmas song: open fire? pollution. folks dressed up like eskimos? cultural appropriation

3. holly jolly christmas: kiss her once for me? unwanted advances

4. white christmas? racist

5. santa claus is coming to town: sees you when you’re sleeping? knows when you’re awake? peeping tom stalker

6. most wonderful time of the year: everyone telling you be of good cheer? forced to hide depression

7. rudolph the red-nosed reindeer: bullying

8. it’s beginning to look a lot like christmas: forced gender-specific gifts: dolls for janice and jen and boots and pistols (guns!) for barney and ben

9. santa baby: gold digger, blackmail

10. frosty the snowman: sexist; not a snow woman

11. do you hear what i hear: blatant disregard for the hearing impaired

12. have yourself a merry little christmas: make the yuletide gay? wow, just wow

13. jingle bell rock: giddy up jingle horse, pick up your feet: animal abuse

14. mistletoe and holly: overeating, folks stealing a kiss or two? how did this song ever see the light of day?

15. winter wonderland: parson brown demanding they get married…forced partnership

16. i'll be home for christmas: not if you are homeless. that's just insensitive

17. grandma got ran over by a reindeer: homicide. extremely violent and promotes alcoholism.” it's funny right?!

text:
the sun is setting on 2018. for some of us, it’s the year that we feel like we became statistics. for many of us, it’s another year in our journey to lifelong healing. 🌱☀️
.
wherever you find yourself on the journey, know that you are not alone. there is a community of women who love god and are working out their anger, faith, and trauma all at the same time. 👏🏿
.
you are much more than a statistic. you, your truth, your story matter. 💜
.
you don’t have to wait until the clock ⏰ strikes midnight on december 31st to claim your healing. healing is your birthright—now...join us. 🙏🏿
.
beautiful scars is a storytelling agency focused on trauma healing and resiliency. @weresurthrivors is an online platform for black christian women who are also survivors of childhood sexual abuse and/or male sexual violence. by helping survivors face and name their trauma, we create holistic care plans so they can integrate their sexual violation(s) into their faith journeys. ultimately, we shift survivors from silence to storytelling, so they evolve into anti-sexual abuse advocates within their faith communities.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
why you keep attracting toxic men, what men want and why self-love is key.
.
woke up to this message from a man i dated a while back.
.
"any man that dates you and marries you will be a better lucky man.  i hope he isn’t a dummy like me that messed things up.  wish you the best mar.  you are an amazing woman. take care."
.
here is the thing about this.
.
i’m going to be damn honest.
.
i felt amazing.😍
i felt empowered.💪🏼
i felt “your loss” 💁🏻‍♀️
it elevated my damn ego.🤦🏻‍♀️
.
i’m not going to lie.
.
then i took a moment to reflect and come back down to earth.
.
is not the person who said this to me that made me feel great this morning.
.
or knowing that he realized this way too late.
.
or knowing that is his damn loss and i won’t go back there ever ever.
.
is the knowing i always had in me when i’ve dated anyone that i am enough, worthy and amazing.
.
is the knowing that i feel and believe at my core any man would be lucky to have me.
.
is the knowing that even if it doesn’t work out it is a great lesson and life experience.
.
here is something i've learned from my own journey and the women i help.
.
every man you have encountered and dated always comes back one way or the other.
.
or maybe you keep attracting the same type of men (rules still apply).
.
ex's that are toxic come back because...
.
-they know you!
-they know how to manipulate you and get you mentally and emotionally.
-they know what makes you fall and take them back.
-they simply know you inside out.
-you are probably have also been fragile, naive, vulnerable, weak, easily manipulated, and doormat.
-you probably don't feel confident.
-you probably are unable to speak up for what you want.
-you probably don't know who you are because you lost yourself.
-you probably are confused on how you feel about him, gaslighting, etc.
-you are always in doubt, fear and anxiety.
-you are probably terrified and scared of being alone, so you rather be with him knowing he is not good for you, than being alone.
-you also believe “you are the woman that will change him” and “your love will heal him.”
.
but you know at your core you deserve better, that this isn't for you.
.
continue 👇🏼👇🏼

here is something i have learned from my own journey and the women i help.
.
every man you have encountered and dated always comes back one way or the other.
.
or maybe you keep attracting the same type of men (rules still apply).
.
ex's that are toxic come back because...
.
-they know you!
-they know how to manipulate you and get you mentally and emotionally.
-they know what makes you fall and take them back.
-they simply know you inside out.
-you are probably have also been fragile, naive, vulnerable, weak, easily manipulated, and doormat.
-you probably do not feel confident.
-you probably are unable to speak up for what you want.
-you probably do not know who you are because you lost yourself.
-you probably are confused on how you feel about him, gaslighting, etc.
-you are always in doubt, fear and anxiety.
-you are probably terrified and scared of being alone, so you rather be with him knowing he is not good for you, than being alone.
-you also believe “you are the woman that will change him” and “your love will heal him.”
.
but you know at your core you deserve better, that this is not for you.
.
continue 👇🏼👇🏼

as part of the 16 days of activism, we are continuing to emphasize and pay tribute to every woman, man, and organization working to challenge violence against women. gender based violence is one of the most pervasive and least-recognized human rights abuses in the world. there are no boundaries of geography—this is a world wide issue, and often these cases are hidden, and the victims suffer in silence. this #womencrushwednesday we want to do our part and help call attention to the ongoing campaign to stop the violence. .
.

text:
classic christmas song, "baby, it's cold outside," is getting a chilly response from canadian radio stations.

according to reports, at least two of the country's biggest media giants (rogers media and bell media) have pulled the song out of rotation, in the wake of the #metoo movement.

the song written back in 1944, has been facing scrutiny over what some say are inappropriate lyrics.

some of the lyrics say the following:

i simply must go (but baby, it's cold outside)
the answer is no (but baby, it's cold outside)

the neighbors might think (baby, it's bad out there)
say what's in this drink? (no cabs to be had out there)

so really i'd better scurry (beautiful please don't hurry)
but maybe just a half a drink more (put some records on while i pour)

what are your thoughts on the lyrics/song? tell us below!

whole concept is stemmed from the media. with a constant reminder that a lighter skinned person would be a better face for a movie or a tv show rather than the culturally appropriate actor/actress. we’ve seen this countless of times in movies, for a recent example; “the hate u give” is a civil rights movie based on a book, the book portrays the leading character, starr, as a dark skin teenage girl, while in the movie starr is represented by a very light skinned african american girl.” -jose, from missouri
