text:
when you are a litigator, friends tend to send problems your way. how do we hire a nanny lawfully? am i being discriminated against—or is my boss just toxic? can my landlord really push me out of my apartment like this? the calls i’ve gotten range from face-palming to jaw-dropping. but nothing prepared me for today.
....
i don’t know her name. but i know that a friend of a friend of a friend was raped. in a livery cab. by her driver. while she was unconscious. and when she came to, he tossed her out of the car, boots askew. and when she reported the rape to the police, the officer told her there were no charges to be brought because she never said no. if that sounds ethically and legally wrong to you, that’s because it is on both counts. in new york, rape by legal definition includes sex with anyone who is physically incapable of consent, a category that includes unconsciousness.
....
after harvey and matt and les, i figured #metoo would reverberate from studios to station houses. but the basic elements of rape and sexual assault are still deeply misunderstood and perverted by law enforcement—and a predator masquerading as a safe ride home is on the loose in brooklyn. the night of her assault, his car was outside the bar with his lights on for about 20 minutes. ask yourself why. in our electric city, who among us has not lost a cab because of supposed sloth? no one. this guy was not actively seeking a fare; no, he was lying in wait.
....
if you or anyone you love is the victim of a sexual assault, please call @rainn for confidential, expert guidance and consult their website on your state’s laws (link in bio). you matter. and unless and until you say yes, no one has your consent. #consent #endrapeculture #youmatter #metoo

blessed to be alive & healthy! as i turn younger and younger :) i realize life is about smiling more, laughing more, less social media, more reading, more of being outside, more of helping others,being nice to strangers, forgive more often, don’t worry about the small stuff, less about shopping, spending time with family, writing thank you cards,  celebrate others, checking on friends more often, saying please & thank you, being more discipline, travel more, praying more, having more faith, choosing more of god and less of me, dying to self, less of my insecurities and accepting my weaknesses, less of what the world says and more what god says, more of acknowledging and accepting others despite of how they look, listening more then speaking, take risk, hugggg moreee(i know the #metoo movement makes you scare of that) and love on others (let them think she’s weird hahaha)... we don’t know the day god will call us home but in the meantime i keep working on the assignment that god has given me! thank you god you have been soooo good to me! #bdaygirl #31yearsyoung #olderbutwiser #childofgod

text:
"she had a real effervescent personality. you wouldn't forget her, that's for sure" - andrew jarvis

like a freshly opened bottle of champagne, our 2nd survivor, bryn lit up the survivor series team! bryn lives many lives, including one as a formerly trained opera singer, the world's best beverage curator, pottery goddess, fashion icon and womanist. we chose this #bts picture of bryn because we think it perfectly captures her vibrant and bubbly strength. advocating for human rights is tough and emotionally draining, but bryn is unwavering in her fight for justice and equality for all humans - especially survivors of sexual violence -  and we're proud to feature her in survivor series: volume i

text: #metoo founder, tarana burke is a powerful blessing! this quote is taken from her recent interview with @nationmag. the full interview is available online & is linked in my bio @thejoyexpert. ms. burke speaks about how parents can support their children after sexual assault. she shares what she learned from parenting her daughter. when asked, “how do we talk to our children about sexual violence, but also help them understand they can find pleasure and joy in their bodies?” ms. burke concludes, “this was a hard one and i struggled with it all through my daughter’s preteen years... i think nonsexual pleasure is one of the main entry points to talk about it, too: nonsexual pleasure in your body. we talk about joy a lot in our family, because it’s central to my work...teaching your child to curate joy in their life very early.”

text:
the year 2008; when ghana had just one shopping mall (koala doesn't count), a time when the word cool didn't really vibe with anything. even our music videos back then were very very uncool.

there were no online trends to follow, no smartphones to make our lives more colorful (i mean all we had was cell phones with #polyphonic ringtones & mp3 players), no posting of pics to get the most likes [even with #myspace], no #dms to slide in, no social media challenges, the #metoo movement wasn't a thing, uber & taxify were unheard of, no jumia foods and waakye guy guy to order from, mobile money didn't even exist chaaaley . there wasn't even a cool concept store to get fun & amazing stuff from.

and then....

text:
#miamimenews 
радиостанция огайо перестала ставить в эфире классическую праздничную композицию "baby, it's cold outside" после жалоб слушателей на оттенки абьюза в песне. wdok-fm в кливленде убрала песню из своего праздничного плейлиста после полученного звонка от слушателя, который счел песню неуместной, особенно в разгар движения #metoo. песня, написанная в 1944 году, рассказывает историю человека, пытающегося убедить свою гостью остаться с ним, пока идет снег. однако она по-прежнему колеблется и отвергает его ухаживания. подробнее на сайте: miami-me.com - ссылка в профиле

text:
culture & arts
in a crowded theater, she accused neil degrasse tyson of rape. eight years later, her story is news.
what tchiya amet began in 2010 reached a kind of fruition last week when two other women came forward with allegations of sexual misconduct.
by bill bradley

her mic cut out before she had finished accusing neil degrasse tyson of sexual assault, but tchiya amet el maat went on anyway, talking loudly enough that even people in the back of the theater got the message. “i don’t know how i did that,” amet, now a natural health therapist and wellness coach, told huffpost recently. “i have a very soft voice.” it was april 21, 2010. tyson was doing a q&a segment at a nova sciencenow cosmic conversation event at san francisco’s palace of fine arts theatre. there, in front of a live audience, with “nova” executive producer paula apsell watching, amet confronted the famous astrophysicist. “i’m here in honor of all the people that you raped, assaulted, harassed, violated, denied,” she said, “and for the lives that you affected and for the lives of their parents and their friends and everyone that was involved when you were a ta in grad school at ut austin in 1984 ― including myself.” to our knowledge, the incident received no media attention. amet could’ve sworn the event was taped, but no broadcast exists. “nova” “doesn’t have recorded footage of that event,” a representative of roslan & campion pr firm said. as far as anyone not in the theater that day was concerned, the first public accusation of sexual misconduct against neil degrasse tyson simply never happened

text:
a coluna de hoje é uma reflexão dura, mas necessária. e convido todos a ler e opinar. 
por que o movimento feminista precisa fugir da vitimização. 
um dos motivos é o efeito rebote do #metoo no mercado de trabalho. entre as medidas adotadas pelos homens, nada de jantar com colegas, não sentar ao lado delas em viagens, pedir quartos em andares diferentes em hotéis. chefes têm evitado reuniões a sós com subordinadas.

a barreira que separa uma relação consensual de uma forçada não parece tão clara para muitas mulheres, e acabou gerando episódios duvidosos de denúncias. parte das acusações que se revelaram infundadas mostra que existe confusão e uma certa vitimização na cabeça feminina.

assédio não pode ser tolerado, o problema é a tolerância zero que tem sido praticada para combater o problema. no fim, estamos criando mulheres infantilizadas, apavoradas com qualquer tipo de aproximação, incapazes de lidar com uma relação, sem se sentirem sempre vulneráveis.

text:
témoignage - viol conjugal
à la suite de mon accouchement, j’ai été assez surprise de me retrouver totalement dénigrée et rejetée par mon cher et tendre. 
les choses sont ce qu’elles sont et je serre les dents. je l’aime, c’est le père de mon enfant, ça finira par aller mieux…ça prend du temps, un an que ça dure, mais bon ça n’est pas facile pour lui. la demande en mariage que j’espérais depuis 7 ans arrive ! ok ça se passe très mal entre nous, mais il m’aime, la preuve, il accepte enfin de faire sa demande.

sans surprise la préparation du mariage se passe terriblement mal… a ce moment-là, un collègue commence à me regarder de près, il ne me dit pas que je suis débile, il est gentil. ça n’est peut-être pas obligatoire de se faire trainer dans la boue ? une chose en entraînant une autre, je finis par passer une nuit avec mon collègue. il ne se passe rien, on dort juste dans les bras l’un de l’autre en se faisant des promesses qui ne seront jamais tenues. 
le lendemain je rentre chez moi avec la ferme intention de quitter mon mec. cette vie n’est plus possible. et ce qui doit arriver arrive. mon mec se met à pleurer, il m’aime, comment j’ai pu le trahir comme ça ? il avait confiance en moi, c’est pour ça qu’il ne vient jamais avec moi. je me sens tellement minable, c’est vrai on devait se marier, et puis en plus on a un enfant. il me voit me décomposer petit à petit. il se rapproche et veut coucher avec moi. je refuse, ça n’est pas le moment. il se fait insistant, après tout je l’ai trompé, je lui dois bien ça. je me sens tellement fatiguée et minable. il insiste encore et encore, jusqu’au moment où j’arrête de dire non. 
s’en suis un acte brutal, il me fait mal, mais vu que je suis une salope je ne peux rien dire. il me tient par les cheveux et me fait baisser la tête. je n’ai pas le sentiment qu’on fait l’amour, d’ailleurs ça n’est pas ce qu’on fait. il est en train de me soumettre à grand coup de sexe. mais vraiment je ne peux rien dire, il m’aime et j’ai failli le tromper cette nuit…

#viol #metoo #femme #viedefemme #combatdesfemmes #violence #mariage #couple #respect #violconjugual #badgalcrew

les choses sont ce qu’elles sont et je serre les dents. je l’aime, c’est le père de mon enfant, ça finira par aller mieux…ça prend du temps, un an que ça dure, mais bon ça n’est pas facile pour lui. la demande en mariage que j’espérais depuis 7 ans arrive ! ok ça se passe très mal entre nous, mais il m’aime, la preuve, il accepte enfin de faire sa demande.

sans surprise la préparation du mariage se passe terriblement mal… a ce moment-là, un collègue commence à me regarder de près, il ne me dit pas que je suis débile, il est gentil. ça n’est peut-être pas obligatoire de se faire trainer dans la boue ? une chose en entraît une autre, je finis par passer une nuit avec mon collègue. il ne se passe rien, on dort juste dans les bras l’un de l’autre en se faisant des promesses qui ne seront jamais tenues. 
le lendemain je rentre chez moi avec la ferme intention de quitter mon mec. cette vie n’est plus possible. et ce qui doit arriver arrive. mon mec se met à pleurer, il m’aime, comment j’ai pu le trahir comme ça ? il avait confiance en moi, c’est pour ça qu’il ne vient jamais avec moi. je me sens tellement minable, c’est vrai on devait se marier, et puis en plus on a un enfant. il me voit me décomposer petit à petit. il se rapproche et veut coucher avec moi. je refuse, ça n’est pas le moment. il se fait insistant, après tout je l’ai trompé, je lui dois bien ça. je me sens tellement fatiguée et minable. il insiste encore et encore, jusqu’au moment où j’arrête de dire non. 
s’en suis un acte brutal, il me fait mal, mais vu que je suis une salope je ne peux rien dire. il me tient par les cheveux et me fait baisser la tête. je n’ai pas le sentiment qu’on fait l’amour, d’ailleurs ça n’est pas ce qu’on fait. il est en train de me soumettre à grand coup de sexe. mais vraiment je ne peux rien dire, il m’aime et j’ai failli le tromper cette nuit…

#viol #metoo #femme #viedefemme #combatdesfemmes #violence #mariage #couple #respect #violconjugual #badgalcrew 
la suite en commentaire 👇

text: i’m doing all the things i wanted to do and bipolar stopped me. swimming with the sea lions 🎯. it’s so frightening when you don’t know what’s happening. before i sorted the spiritual influence out, i was full of fears. kept saying, “when i meet the right person”, “when i’m in the right situation”, “when i’m ready”. but when, how do we know whether we’re ready? each time depression (i mainly had depression) hit me, after that was a breakthrough. stand strong, a breakdown is before the breakthrough. the creator loves you and wants the best for you! although it’s so hard to see it then, until i understood the love of the universe. how well-loved i am. i’m fighting seasonal allergies and my face is like an inflatable bouncy castle, one day bloated, one day ok. 🤷🏻‍♀️ my spirits are still up, i’m still going and i’m never gonna stop. ❤️💫🙏🏻 #depression #bipolar #mentalhealth #breakthrough #metoo #ptsd

text:
who’s to blame|i was 5 years old, surrounded by a loving family who loved god and loved people. i can still remember the dress that my mom dressed me in on that sunday morning. it was a yellow dress with frills and ruffles. my hair done in perfect braids adorned with yellow barrettes. on this particular sunday, at the beginning of the church service, i had to go to the bathroom. 
i made my way down the stairs to the bathroom, upon exiting i found myself being abruptly picked up and pushed up against the wall. confused & disoriented, i finally realized that i was being held by a young man that apparently followed me and waited for me. he proceeded to pull my dress up. i remember the lace that was sown around the trim of my dress. he placed his hand in my panties and began to touch me. i was left feeling scared & confused. he continued to molest me for some time after that day which started to seem like it was a regular part of life. during that time i kept what was happening a secret as i was afraid i would be judged. soon came more young men that began to molest me. i started to think that there was a stamp on my forehead that said: “touch her.” i was molested until the age of 11 years old. the years that followed, i carried the guilt of that pain. i didn’t love who i saw in the mirror, and i blamed myself for what happened to me. i started to have low self-esteem, i cried a lot, and i believed i wasn’t good enough. now that i am an adult, whose to blame for what happened to me??? for years i blamed myself and believed i was the cause of the trauma that happened to me. but why do we do this to ourselves. why do we blame the victim. why do we then point fingers at them for not telling what happened to them until years later. why do we shame them? why do we point fingers? so i ask whose to blame, the 5 year old in this photo or....... @metoomvmt @timesupnow #survivor #notavictim of #sexualabuse #beyondthebarriers of #depression there is #hope #selflove #selfcare #melaningirlmovement #hopestillstands @essence  @redtabletalk #metoo #timesup #bmore #dc #dmv #baltimore

text:
i had to take a minute to look at myself. to see myself from the outside. to see the face of a girl who has survived numerous traumas and is still pushing forward. i wish i could feel it more, but i want to tell her i'm proud of her and that she's kind, compassionate and principled...in spite of abuse and rape, and people not always being so kind to her. i wanted to remind her that she's empathetic and brave, and that it's okay to hurt.

text:
⏳ the rise of internet changed the way we protest. authors divide the history of activism in three periods :
“activism before cyberspace : in this period, actors are local and their engagement is physical, the flow of information is slower and restricted to traditional media, social movements are organized around leaders and the interaction with citizens is lower than today’s activism.
cyberactivism 1.0 : this time actors may be international or regional and their engagement is still offline. social movements have more horizontal organization attached either to the ngos or a leader. beside traditional media, e-mail and websites remain the main communication tools though the flow of information is still restricted and limited to organizers. unlike the previous period, the interaction between citizens is partially online and offline.
cyberactivism 2.0 : today’s activists are globally and horizontally self-organized. their engagement is online, instant and permanent. they communicate through social media and there is a constant flow information. they engage mostly online and partially also offline.” [23]
📱the usual channels cyber-activists use were social media or blogs. but what we see more and more in digital activism is the use of podcasts.
🎙 a podcast that illustrates this new tool is @yessspodcast. in the latest episode (05/12/18), one of the co-host said that after #metoo, we heard a lot of testimonies about what women live(d) but now, what? what can we do as “normal” citizens? she explained that their podcast was made to share concrete strategies women can use to try to escape harassment or help someone in trouble. the podcast is also there to try to change the social point of view as we often talk about victims and rarely about the other part of the aggression (the culprit). so the podcast aims to make people think about the why of those actions, it aims to talk about patriarchy, about toxic masculinity, etc. (personal translation) [24].
📸 https://twitter.com/yessspodcast 🔗 [23] https://www.academia.edu/20008041/_paradigms_in_digital_activism_ [24] https://apple.co/2eeyjqk
#digipoluclouvain #activism #socialactivism #digitalactivism #cyberactivism #feminism

text:
equality bootcamp in lund, sweden – may 2018

lærke, sydslesvig: (📷: @laerke.rahr)
nsus main theme in 2018 is equality, and it is deeply rooted in gender equality. 
in november 2017 the viral #metoo movement was born, and countless survivors of sexual abuse and violence have spoken up about their experiences since. the discussion about gender and the power attributed to it, is more present in the media and our daily lives than ever. 
the “nordic lifestyle” is often praised in the media for its good healthcare and school systems. but how much equality does the north really have? 
this is where nsu has been aiming its focus towards this year - to ask the difficult questions about inequality in the nordic countries. are national and sexual minorities in the nordic countries treated with the same respect as the majority? how do we ensure integration for the people, who need it the most? how do we include those, who have less? is equality or equity the best tool? how do we practice a good example at home in our youth organisations?

the youth of the north have had the opportunity to discuss these matters together during the events of this year, and to come up with possible solutions on a local level. it is important to recognize the inequality that plays out right in front of our eyes, and to do something about it. 
#nsu#nordiskeunge#unginorden

the youth of the noh have had the oppounity to discuss these matters together during the events of this year, and to come up with possible solutions on a local level. it is impoant to recognize the inequality that plays out right in front of our eyes, and to do something about it.

text:
in honour of today, the national day of remembrance and action on violence against women, i want to share a story, and a resource that has been so influential for my healing journey. this isn’t easy to do, but i hope that it can raise awareness and provide support for those who may need it, even if just one person can feel less alone. 
tw: sexualized violence, sexual assault •
•
•
•
•
•
•
4 months ago, i was drugged in an environment i perceived to be safe, while out with coworkers in downtown victoria. i woke up 8 hours later in a hospital, in pain, injured, and with no memory . 
thankfully, a friend took me to the victoria sexual assault centre, where i received immediate support. they have provided me with long-term counselling for free (which they offer for immediate trauma or any previous trauma for anyone). i don’t know how i would have gotten through this without their services, and without the support of my friends and family. i am eternally grateful. 
currently, every day is a new battle, and every aspect of my life is different, but the counsellors at the vsac have been there to guide me through it. it makes me sick to know that this is continuing to happen to women worldwide. 
it’s time to fucking stand up, raise our voices for those who can’t, and say enough is enough. believe survivors, advocate for survivors, and hold people to a higher standard. 
to anyone struggling today or any day, i am here to talk, always ❤️ #metoo #believewomen

text:
i love this!
construction workers in manila breaking through constructed stereotypes.
“man up!”
“another case of, man-flu?!”
as unintentionally offensive as these phrases and the like are, they are the roots causing difficulty for men to take responsibility for their health! 
the falsely constructed image of, ‘masculinity’, is based upon physical strength and yet we, as a society, penalise each man for making health conscious decisions: skincare, meditation, yoga, stretching, etc. we claim that they’re, ‘feminine things’! all we are achieving here is clearly defined gender-roles and an impossibility for us, as a society, to cohabit in freedom, opportunity, peace and trust... let’s change this together. 
here, construction workers execute a choreographed, morning stretch routine before beginning their day as builders. 
builder - ‘a man’s job’...

text: five things about me: 1) i was 14 the first time i got stoned 2) that same year i was raped by a 21 year old 3) at 19 i was lost in a physically abusive relationship 4) the following year i got pregnant and had an abortion (thank god for #plannedparenthood!) i had to borrow money for the procedure. i have detached myself from these memories so that i could survive the pain, confusion, and shame they bring up for me. 5) it wasn’t until i met my husband that i truly began to believe a life full of joy and happiness, and satisfaction was available for me. integrating that young woman with who i am today is empowering and healing. sharing my story reminds me that life is not so different for any of us — we all have what it takes to overcome our required challenges. #fivethingsaboutme #decemberreflections2018 #day5 #metoo #strong #mymessybeautifullife (thank you @susannahconway for the prompt!)

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

text:
what art has taught me - day 4: leave your authentic mark on the world. 💛💛💛🧡💛💛💛 this is the first painting i created as an adult. i was trying to paint a dream,where a beautiful, radiant goddess had come to me. i couldn't figure out how to make her glow. discouraged i covered the yellow with muddy brown. jackson pollack said-- "i have no fears about making changes, destroying the image, etc., because the painting has a life of its own”. i accepted that i had made a mess of my painting (and perhaps, my life) and surrendered to that truth. i greeted my shadow but, unlike pollock, this new painter was afraid, but not totally repulsed.  the muddy brown entombed the ancient goddess and guardian. something magical happened and the surrounding darkness made  the goddess glow.  golden protection was added and she radiated out of the canvas and her eternal dance continued. 
this painting and the experience of co-creating her, created a movement, a quickening, in me that is beyond words.  following the voice with integrity, disintegrating the self, adding to the canvas, supporting it with the guardian… beyond words-preverbal. seeing my handprint, my mark on the world, i had a sense of both my gentle uniqueness and the timelessness - oneness of soul.  i alone was acquainted with the depths and the beauty in her layers. 🙏🏼🙏🏽🙏🏾🙏🏿🙏🏻 #sacred #soul #painting #intuitive #ancient #cavepainting #intuition #goddess #wisdom #integrity #womenspower #metoo #goddess #sacredfeminine #dreams #mixedmedia #risingpower #tarot #wicca #hopi #secrets #raven #magic #truth #art #jungian #gaia #medicine #healing #authentic #truth

text:
had a really good yoga class which was really nice... and somewhat unexpected as i was in a horrible head space.
🙏

shortly before lunch - and my noontime yoga - a song came on. it's a beautiful song. i love it..... loved it. today it caused such an anxiety attack that i wasn't sure if i'd survive. it was horrible!
💧

it took me back to the summer of 2016 at "the event of the summer" that i look forward to it every year. it was this same song that played that brought up memories of my dad - who had passed away almost exactly 3 months previous. i excused myself and ran off  for privacy so i could have a cry and not have to listen to the song. 💧

after i returned to the party, i started drinking. partially to numb my feelings, and partially to have a good time.
💧

things went bad. real bad.
💧

by the time i realized that i drank way too much, it was too late.
💧

i have so much shame over that whole incident. more happened, but i can't go there right now. that song didn't trigger me to the end of the evening and the assault; it triggered me to the point of the evening that i made the decision to start drinking to forget. 💧

i find it so hard to move on; to get over it and relax around the people who were there. i spoke with a couple of them after - to explain and apologize but sometimes it doesn't feel like enough. 💧

the important part is i feel better... at the moment. that insane anxiety from earlier has been replaced by shame and guilt which i deal with on a somewhat regular basis from that day.
💧

shame is normal. we all feel shame now and then for different reasons at different intensities. it shouldn't be shut away as it won't go away unless you talk about it. 💧

that's why i decided to share.
🙏

#shame #shaming #anxiety #anxietyattack #alcoholabuse #memories #replayingbadmemories #noshameinshame #livingopenly #mentalhealth #letstalk #metoo #sexualassault #bingedrinking #goingsober #sobriety #loveyourself #everydaycourage #everythingwillbeokay #panicattack #regrets #poorchoices #imsorry

@regran_ed from @warif_ng -  december 05 | day 11

let’s talk about victim blaming 
a common response to rape and sexual assault in our society is to blame the survivor. to assume that the fault lies with her based on her choices and in some cases her lifestyle.  it is often heard that she could have prevented the assault if only:
“she dressed differently”
“she was in the company of others”
“she stayed home after dark”
“she wasn’t so friendly”

this focus places the responsibility of the prevention of sexual violence and rape solely on young girls and women and not on the perpetrators, where it belongs.

let’s stop blaming her when we need to encourage her.

share our stories , repost , tag someone and join us in the #orangetheworldwithwarif campaign as we participate in the #16daysofactivism against gender based violence.

text:
today is my 19th birthday. this past year, like many before it, had many trials. there has been several times where i felt close to giving up and ending it, or that things were so hopeless that i needed a hero to save me. so this year i decided to end the hopelessness and became my own hero. i saved myself and no matter how long it takes or how hard i have to work to get there, i will rise. 
this is my birthday present to myself as well as a reminder to any of you out there who may be struggling right now that it will get better, but to do so you have to fight like hell. fight. grow. succeed. and to any of you who may share my birthday, happy birthday!!!!! #birthday #artistsoninstagram #art #watercolor #selfportriat #me #growthmindset🌱 #growthmindset #growth #journey #portrait #mentalhealth #metoo #mentalhealthawareness #colorpencil #clouds #pink #pinkclouds

@arimelber @donlemoncnn @seanhannity @maddowshow @thejimmydoreshow @cnn @nbcnews bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text: if you have been hurt, if your story has been questioned, if you’ve been victimized, assaulted, harassed...if you’ve waited and wondered what good it would do to speak up...this is for you. back then, i didn’t feel brave, i felt terrified. i didn’t feel heard, i felt re-traumatized. i am still very, very angry. but i am overjoyed to have this essay published on #therumpus, because it feels like my rage is becoming recovery. maybe it’s time to hand the shame back to the men who created it. link in profile ❤️ #metoo #timesup #takethelead #believewomen #believesurvivors

text: in the age of #metoo, this could not have been a timelier read. i happened to read this the same week as the kavanaugh hearings and was struck by how prescient @emilygiffinauthor was when she conceived this novel. in all we ever wanted, two parents navigate doing right by their child (and doing right may not always mean what one thinks it should mean) after one photograph alters everything. the depth and heart and tenderness of this book had me reading it with my hand over my open mouth, identifying with so much of what was happening and haunted by the echoes of the real-life hearings going on at the same time. absorbing and thought-provoking.  #rosiereads

@arimelber @donlemoncnn @seanhannity @maddowshow @thejimmydoreshow @cnn @nbcnews bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin

text: “way back when wednesday” obviously i’m late to the “old headshot” day posts, but i was pulling out christmas crap & decorations & found this photo 📷 my first headshot ever at age 18! i don’t remember the photographer’s name to give him credit. ( he was dating michelle pfeiffer’s sister at the time & i was very impressed by that 😂) it was the very first shot of the day & that ended up being the one my agent liked the most. i booked some commercials, a music video, a cheesy tv show, & got a line in a movie & sag eligible w/ this picture. i still have the @tiffanyandco silver heart necklace i wore in this photo. it’s in black & white because color head shots weren’t really around yet ... 🤔 i had a pager for auditions & used to have to pull over to find pay phones to call back for details. cell phones weren’t around either. 🙀i’m so old! 🙄 anyways: what i would tell my 18 year old self is to: put myself out there, pursue your dreams & don’t waste so much time on boys! i was so insecure & spent too much time in acting school when i should have been auditioning & hustling in plays & actually working! i kept reading / auditioning for leads in movies when i should have been playing cheerleader #1 just to get some on set experience! i hated working in the modeling industry because i was constantly told that i should model & then when i did, people picked me apart, told me to lose weight w/ cocaine & constantly insulted me while simultaneously hitting on me.... but acting was great & although there were always creepy “producers” that i just avoided... i felt that i could be more of myself & participate in creative projects without compromising my dignity. my life took me in a different direction & i had kids & never returned to pursue what i loved.... i’m writing a script now. life goes by fast & it’s ok to put dreams on hold for awhile. don’t give up your creative pursuits just because you aren’t 18 anymore... there is only one you in the world 🌎 w/ your voice ✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨#thisis18 #longtimeago #nytgender #girlgaze #oldheadshot #metoo #beforeinstagram #backintheday #faith

text: i read somewhere recently that photography was the fine art of this century. i can agree. for me though, photography doesn’t offer the release that painting does. the process of painting flows through me. so, learning to alter my images further, with photography, maybe that’s what i offer fine art of this century. at any rate, i have acrylic originals as well as photo altered prints. that’s cool. and speaking of cool we had our first hard frost here on the west coast last night. brrrrr.

text: it must be noted that women did not experience complete social liberation, although this newfound intellectual enlightenment was the first step into gaining social reform. it would be foolish to consider their intellectual liberation without consideration of female authorship; women were published at a higher rate in circulating libraries than independent publishing companies, which furthered their intellectual liberation, for they were given the opportunity to construct their own novels. women were of course met with disapproval and criticism, yet this did not heed the grandiose opportunities women were met with as a result of the circulating libraries.

text: thank you @nyc_hub for hosting creative responses to the #metoo movement. it’s remarkable that “sexual harassment” didn’t even have a name until 1975. we’ve made progress, but we still have a long way to go. independent contractors, specifically, remain uniquely vulnerable. we don’t have hr, we’re excluded from title vii of the civil rights act, and nys human rights law, which was amended recently to protect contractors, still falls short. employers have the power to end the harassment on their watch, but it’s going to take more than window dressing and it shouldn’t have to take lawsuits or bad press either. @modelallianceny has been working to bring real change to the fashion industry through a private sector initiative called the respect program, which we discussed at last night’s panel. respect uses a tested approach that’s proved to be hugely effective in other industries; it’s held up as the “model” program that should be adopted more widely. enough survivors have taken the painful step of coming forward. we need to honor them and make sure they haven’t done so in vain. #time4respect
name: Sara Ziff

text:
when women come together, magic happens.. .
.
the past weekend we were in the company of africa's most inspiring and powerful women at the @motsepefoundation sdg5 breakfast. some, we are fortunate enough to have as our advisors. .
.
we were inspired by keynotes, panel discussions and the presence of thought leaders such as un deputy secretary general, amina mohammed, graca machel, thuli madonsela, and our amazing wef family,  rapelang rabana, naadiya moosajie among others.
.
.
thank you dr precious motsepe and the motsepe foundation for hosting this beautiful event. we look forward to working together to accelerate progress on sdg5 by 2030 and onwards. .
.
"freedom cannot be achieved unless women have been emancipated from all forms of oppression". (nelson mandela)

text:
"i am not fighting for my kingdom and wealth now. i am fighting as an ordinary person for my lost freedom, my bruised body, and my outraged daughters."
.

boudica was a queen of the british celtic iceni tribe who led an uprising against the occupying forces of the roman empire in ad 60 or 61. boudica's husband, prasutugus, ruled as a nominally-independent ally of rome, when he died his will left his kingdom to his daughters. however this was ignored and his properties were annexed. according to tacitus, boudica was flogged and her daughters raped. boudica led a very large army of iceni, trinovantes, and others to defeat a detachment of legio ix hispana, and they burned and destroyed londinium and verulamiam. an estimated 70,000–80,000 romans and british were then killed in the three cities by those led by boudica, many by torture.
.

text:
« merci de me laisser parler aujourd'hui. si je devais trouver des excuses à mes agresseurs, je vous dirais que ce qu’il s’est passé n'est pas grave.  ma place de femme fait de moi une victime de la société. c’est une certitude, la femme étant inférieure à l’homme, je ne devrais même pas m’exprimer devant vous. je devrais être placée au pilori et fouettée pour mon insolence. 
être battue est quelques choses de bien commun pour une personne appartenant au sexe féminin. si la femme a été créée ne serait-ce pas fait pour ça ? 
les bleus sur mon corps ne font qu’un tableau d’art sans importance. mes jambes portent un nuancier passant du bleu au violet et même au noir. comment pourrai-je me plaindre alors que je porte un tableau de van-gogh sur mon informe joli corps ? 
mon statut de jeune femme me confère un pouvoir inégalable nommé le silence. se taire et se laisser faire.
me voilà bien triste d’être devant vous, à vous prier votre indulgence. je vous laisse juge de mon corps qui est lui déjà regardé sans amour ni intérêt, juste pour ce qu’il est : de la chaire. je suis un morceau de chair avec une âme vagabondant à l’intérieur depuis que j’ai perdu ma part d’innocence. une âme déshonorée, salie par des mains, des regards, des souffles dénués de sentiments et d’amour propre. 
je suis une femme aussi faible qu’une pâquerette écrasée pour oser me montrer devant vous. comment leur en vouloir alors que je ne portais qu’un jean, un pull et un manteau ? c’était d’une vulgarité que cela devait être puni par une personne supérieure à moi, l’homme. l’homme ! une création divine que l’on ne peut remettre en question. cette créature d’une beauté légendaire, d’une force monstrueuse et d’un pouvoir à faire pâlir les dieux.
je l’ai mérité. j’ai mérité les coups et les insultes. oui. j’ai refusé cet homme, mais, avais-je ce droit ? il ne m’a pas proposée, il m’a obligée. alors je n’ai rien dit. j’ai fermé les yeux et je suis partie, laissant mon corps allongé sur le sol aussi froid que mon cœur. et tout le monde sait que ne rien dire veut dire oui, sinon, ce serait illégal. mais qui faut-il blâmer moi, cet homme ou la société ? » ©
#metoo #noustoutes

je suis une femme aussi faible qu’une pâquerette écrasée pour oser me montrer devant vous. comment leur en vouloir alors que je ne poais qu’un jean, un pull et un manteau ? c’était d’une vulgarité que cela devait être puni par une personne supérieure à moi, l’homme. l’homme ! une création divine que l’on ne peut remettre en question. cette créature d’une beauté légendaire, d’une force monstrueuse et d’un pouvoir à faire pâlir les dieux.
je l’ai mérité. j’ai mérité les coups et les insultes. oui. j’ai refusé cet homme, mais, avais-je ce droit ? il ne m’a pas proposée, il m’a obligée. alors je n’ai rien dit. j’ai fermé les yeux et je suis paie, laissant mon corps allongé sur le sol aussi froid que mon cœur. et tout le monde sait que ne rien dire veut dire oui, sinon, ce serait illégal. mais qui faut-il blâmer moi, cet homme ou la société ? » ©

at the centro congressi @fondazione_cariplo  in #milan. “knockin’ on heaven’s door” will address greek mythology through a workshow presented by francesca isola and laura strazzeri, who will illustrate the extraordinary powers of greece’s gods and goddesses, as metaphor of both men and women everyday professional and personal challenges.

text: back in february i was diagnosed with major clinical depression, ptsd, and general anxiety disorder. leading up to that diagnosis i was struggling a lot just to get through a day and was very close to being involuntarily admitted for 72 hours by the time my mom dragged me to get help. however, one day during what i  call my ‘spiral’ i had a good day which is when i took this picture and have held onto it for over a year now. i don’t know how i did it, but i took a picture that made me feel powerful, sexy, womanly, independent, and strong at a time where i felt like anything but that. even though there is a 20 to 30 pound difference between this picture and where i am now i thought it was the perfect picture to end the small collection of before pictures i have been sharing over the past few days.

text: my best friend/a brother. um it is the day before tomorrow in a future sense of the past. this post talk will get weird. starting to feel like that's not home anymore, it'll always be home in some ways, although so much has changed i will not live there. about cities and towns and moving while adult...kinda adult. lived in the twin cities a bit, and it's weird the versus of alternating currents via minneapolis/st paul. 2 years and a month or so in, recognising this could be a home town to be from temporary or permanent depending on life. very large cities around here. happy to live on the block i am. alternating currents between those cities as well. from origins to mentalities to pronunciation, ect. i like where i work. i like where i am sometimes. it's a home cooking family jam. to know that these are people with established lives here. as we enter each others lives it gets confusing. i've never worked for you before, yet you are as if in an alternate universe 1000 miles from, foster mom, best friend, the veterinarian, and they've all just been living out here. diversity is very important for many reasons including ptsd and welcoming new ways of life, along with all the awesomeness. we live in a house made of each other. #freepress #metoo #blacklivesmatter #waterprotectors #home #timeandspace #alternatingcurrents #alternateuniverse #donthitpeopleintheheadandtakeawayhealthcare #survivingdoesntmeanhealthyliving

text:
i saw an old friend yesterday that i am no longer friends with out and about downtown. they never saw me. i was driving in my car, they were walking on the sidewalk and we were both going in the same direction. honestly, it was kind of mind boggling to come face to face with their existence because i forgot for a while they even existed. ➡️you know when that happens?⬅️
i say old friend because we’re not friends anymore. this person exploited me under the guise of being an “artist” and totally violated my trust. my body. our friendship.
.
when i saw them out and about, all these feelings rose to the surface and bombarded me with images, feelings, and events that i stuffed down at the time. i started shaking and wanted to cry. i went home and kept asking myself, why did the universe want me to see them? why now? and how interesting this person never saw me, i never entered into their reality. we almost collided and crossed paths, but at the last second it changed, they went down another street. the universe just wanted me to see them, not interact. why did all of this happen?
✔️for me to realize i still have feelings about what happened. ✔️to acknowledge i have challenges trusting people and i haven’t healed this yet.
✔️for me to have a true “birds-eye” perspective about the situation with me on the outside seeing them from afar...and to see i truly am better off without their presence in my life.
✔️to remind me: this person and the part they played in my life is still affecting me and i need to do some shedding/releasing so i can heal. truly heal.
➡️if i hadn’t seen them, would i know the information i have now, after seeing them/ processing/giving myself space? it’s only when things get real “front and center” for me, when i’m faced head-on with the healing that is left to do, that i can empower myself to make a change. you have to be aware, conscious of it or it becomes buried to get rediscovered later..
.
i want to trust and love again with an open heart. as i’m sure you can probably tell, this wasn’t the first time someone violated me and my trust, but this one was the one that catalyzed me into developing and creating my business. (continued in comments)⤵️

text:
domestic bliss - 2018
digital 
a woman’s world - week 5
social media has been set alight this week with the #hearmetoo movement. the annual campaign against gender-based violence that runs for 16 days from november 25th until 10th december.

for over a week now, i have been reading and watching social media as it fires up the voices of so many women across the globe. un women produced an interesting article called '16 ways, 16 days: your guide to ending violence against women'. as i read through the article, it said one way to help was to get creative, which of course, was an absolute must for me! so, with orange, the colour of the movement in mind, i made a piece of work called domestic bliss. it is part of my year long project called a woman's world, where i will explore news stories and world issues faced by women in 2018-2019.
#brigitteaiguille #hearmetoo #art #artist #metoo #feminism #feminist #black #orange #womensrights #women #femaleempowerment #equality #contemporaryart #feministartist #tears #abuse #timeisnow #love #truth #passion #abetterworld #dreams #relationships #unwomen #orangetheworldin16days #orangetheworld #violenceagainstwomen #16daysofactivism #awomansworld

text:
some people have come back to me and ask “why do i still have these feelings?” well, my dear, you are going to always feel them until you no longer do. but now that you see it from a different perspective, you respond to it differently and it doesnt control you or cause you to make toxic choices...
healing doesnt mean the trauma or the feelings disappear, it means you able to accept that part of yourself and love it regardless!
#trauma #survivor #ptsd #victimsofabuse #metoo #standup #riseabove #levelup #raiseyourlevel #cheers #letsbefriends #followme

text:
i trade my art for life, most probably because of #yayoikusama 
by chance i bought her #bibliography (ages ago i had a habit to wander around book shops/libraries, just for the sake of finding/meeting the right book), i was completely absorbed in her words, or her world... her determination, her obsession and her madness were insanely attractive/admiring/inspiring; she says "art keeps her alive" #metoo 
to feel how she feels, i sat myself on the gallery floor, drew like her, tried to get the mindset of her #obsessive impulse. it was somewhat meditative. #dotdotdot #victoriamiro #victoriamirogallery #popart #contemporaryart #kusama #infinty #themovingmomentwheniwenttotheuniverse #mirrorroom #bright #popcolour #doodle #draw #onthespot #urbansketch #usk #installation #art 
p.s mirror room, i was monitored by human cctv--- feeling so anxious -i couldn't enjoy at all; 
p.p.s the guy who timed me with a stopwatch; i'd appreciate if he could tell me how much time i could spend inside... alone... beforehand 
p.p.p.s porridge of today features lots of seeds #banana and #driedpineapple @urbanfruituk
p.ppps day5 #christmastree is hidden in my #sketches #visualdiary #minimalism #instakusama #kusamaart

text:
if i was to ask you to stand in front of your mirror and tell me what you see, what’s the first thought that comes to your mind? .
.
is the first thought one of love, or instant criticism? .
.
what if i asked you to post a picture on social media of yourself makeup free, looking just how you do after you wake up?  what’s the first thought that comes to mind?  hell no! right?  have you ever stopped to ask yourself why judgment is the first thing we default to about ourselves?
.
.
when we are born into this world, we are so open to the truth of life. all we see is good, and all we know is that if there’s something we don’t like, we speak up with our screaming voice. if there’s something we love, we turn to it over and over. our eyes are open to adventure and wonder!
.
.
somewhere along the way we become exposed to opinions of others, rules of our parents, and expectations of society. suddenly our eyes of wonder become eyes of criticism and judgment.  the one we judge the most is ourself. we aren’t good enough, fast enough, skinny enough, too many rolls, pimples, and gray hairs. .
.
if we are really unhappy with parts of ourselves - because we were once taught to be - we engage in self harming behavior such as abuse of food, alcohol, sex or cigarettes. the cycle you have been in for most of your life is due to internal criticism, judgment, and lack of acceptance.
.
.
👇🏻👇🏻👇🏻

text: “how do you handle receiving prejudice from your own community? that’s the complexity of colorism: it’s a preference for lighter skin within people of the same racial group. growing up, the only black female celebrities i saw were light-skinned. think beyoncé, rihanna, mariah carey, nicki minaj, tyra banks, halle berry...etc. there was a period in my life where the darkness of my skin made me feel...ugly. i was often told, “you’re pretty for a black girl” or “you’d be even prettier if you were lighter.” a lot of these comments came from black boys, and later men. i had to undergo a mental transformation where i accepted and embraced my features, including my afro textured hair—which i never saw represented. that’s why movies like black panther, and actresses such as lupita nyong’o are so exciting for women who look like me. and things are slowly changing. but whenever i hear rappers talk about wanting a “yellow bone chick”, see that a makeup brand doesn’t have my shade, or read interview dress tips that say “keep hair professional, tidy, combed, and preferably straight”, i wonder if we’ve come that far at all. however, i have hope that the future will be brighter for those blessed with dark skin.” -stella, from missouri

en todo caso y cualquiera que sea la interpretación, el resultado es extraordinario.

text:
yesterday 20.000 people went on the street to fight for an end of violence against women. 
even though austria is the sad leader of femicides in the eu - 32 women killed in 2018 - the demonstrations were not taking place in austria - but israel. 
israel, which has more or less the same number of inhabitants like austria, counts - sadly enough - 27 women killed in 2018. 
these killings mostly take place in a domestic environment. most of the women are killed by their partner or ex-partner.
the thing that strikes me is that i had no idea about the situation in austria. even when the austrian broadcasting agency reported of the demonstrations in tel aviv, they didn‘t connect it to what is going on in austria. i don’t get it.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
"in 2015, out of 68,833,476 registered voters, 45,888,984 were women and yet nigerian women have the lowest representation in political leadership" - inec

_
african women in leadership organisation in partnership with yali lagos organizes the #womendecide awareness walk to pass across the message of women's crucial role in electoral decisionmaking.

this is a sensitization walk on women's political participation as voters and leaders and a face-to-face interaction with community leaders and stakeholders to spark decision making interest amongst women and girls.

we'll walk through ikeja city mall to johnson jakande tinubu park, alausa where would have  a 1 hour information session
date: 15th december 2018
meet up time at ikeja city mall: 7am
come ready in your black or orange tees and blue or black jeans. this will be brief and smooth.

sign up at awlo.org/womendecide to be part of this empowering walk!!

a writer’s soul- with @najwazebian ⁣
⁣
i know you felt that! and so did i. which is why i had to interview the powerful and inspiring trailblazer who coined this phrase, najwa zebian.⁣
⁣
najwa is a celebrated lebanese-canadian poet and inspirational speaker on a mission to change the world.⁣
⁣
in this heart-filled interview, najwa shares her account of witnessing her home in lebanon engulfed in war, to her incredible journey of immigration, vulnerability, invisibility, and self-discovery. ⁣
⁣
on the heels of the #metoomovement we confront head-on the mindset of power dynamics and the reality and effects that men and women are faced with on a daily basis.⁣
⁣

⁣
this woman has shaped and changed her entire life and is now on a mission to change the world. ⁣
⁣
watch/listen now!⁣
⁣

text:
hey you! ya you!  do you know what is the definition of consent? “permission for something to happen or agreement to do something.” want to know why i wrote the definition?  because people tend to ignore it so i figured they wouldn’t know what is means. 
you see the thing this people seem to ignore when someone says no.  a no means a no. not that hard to understand. 
don’t be the pathetic dick head that chases girls even when they say no. it’s sick and disgusting and makes you look like a pervert. 
these articles about harassment we read and think to ourselves “are these stories even real?” i mean we have a reason to doubt since we didn’t experience this, but trust me when i say this, it’s painfully true. everyone gets harassed on a daily basis, few are just to afraid to speak up.  i am here to share my story in hopes to bring light to this situation and make people understand to just take no for an answer and walk away.  read about this further in our blog.  #consent #harassment #nomeansno #metoo  link in bio

my heart got torn to pieces last night after hearing the comments justifying a vote to keep drew nelson as our city’s leader.  with a chamber audience packed, many were left shaken, in tears and had to get up and leave due to the triggering and insensitive comments made by dan shore and cheryl brown kovacic.  this year, drew nelson drunkenly fired 8 rounds in the air in a residential neighborhood in #winterpark #winterparkcolorado and asked his wife to hit him with a sledgehammer while his kids were in the house... he was arrested on domestic violence and weapons charges and ultimately entered a plea guilty on weapons charges.  he resigned from his job there.  the city of #salidacolorado ignored its constituents, ignored the voices at a community forum and voted to keep him, even after three city employees have written letters complaining about his behavior in the workplace.  the city made a horrifying statement last night about its position on leadership qualifications, city role models, #gunviolence #domesticviolence #metoo #metoomovement and basic human safety concerns.  our key vote held by a woman, took this city in a backwards direction.  i am sad today but i am not giving up.  i’m calling on all people here in #salida to continue to bravely take action towards reversing this decision.  i want to thank justin critelli and mike bowers for standing up against #drewnelson i want to thank all the men and women who have spoken up, written letters, sent emails, and raised awareness of this issue.  i’m now calling on #educators and #womensrights leaders #mentalhealth professionals and #guncontrol experts near and far and all local citizens to get involved.  our amazing, incredible mountain town needs you.  we can do better than this.  we don’t want to be the washington redskins, or #lancemason or trump administration of local city governance. we can fix this.  we are the change.  get loud people!! #salidacolorado #winterparkcolorado #colorado #womensrightsmatter #domesticviolenceawareness #gunviolenceawareness #smashthepatriarchy #fightthepatriarchy #votewithyourdollars
name: Megan Rae Kahn

text:
呢件事我上個星期己經想講，但係等到而家先至得閒少少去講出嚟。。。
我係重慶大廈嗰間大家樂嘅管核文員，我留左喺呢間分店大約三個半月（我算留得耐，呢間舖之前有段時間係一個月換一個文員），入職第一個星期喺黃埔一期嗰間受訓，之後到左8月27日就去左重慶大廈嘅分店，頭一個月仲有個高級文員喺度嗰時個經理都未會做d性騷擾行為，亦唔會亂咁叫我做d文員絕對唔可以做嘅野，例如將宣傳物料同原材料由7樓倉搬落去舖頭，亦唔會喺圍數（即係數夾萬入面嘅錢）嗰時借意「i」埋去我個身度。
我嗰間舖嘅office係細過劏房好多，坐兩個人己經好逼，三個人（我、高級文員同經理）更加逼，但係經理都唔會「i」個身埋去高級文員嗰度。
呢一個月，亦係唯一一個月冇比個經理亂搞我嘅時間。
自從高級文員比人調左去另一間舖，而我又正式接手嗰度之後，個pk經理（唔係副經理，係正嗰個經理，男人）就開始愈嚟愈過分，例如喺我同佢都喺office嗰陣時特登「i」埋去我個身度，圍數嗰陣又趁我好專心計數嗰時成個頭拱埋去我隻手度，你i埋去我個身度，我可以當係因為office太細而要咁樣做，但係成個死人頭拱埋去我隻手度又點解釋？前世未見過理科生計數定係未見過計數計得咁快嘅文員？不過高級文員同樣計數計得快，又唔見佢拱個死人頭埋去！我就反而比佢咁樣對待！呢d行為可能對於佢嚟講好正常，但係根本就係有意去非禮人！
我己經冇同佢講我係理科生，亦冇同佢講我算係一個物理科老師，我唔想運用我嘅物理知識去對付一個色狼，而家最慘係個cctv一直都影到佢冇非禮我，但係佢成日都hi到我個身，甚至有時差d掂到我個胸，咁呢d叫咩？唔通又係普通嘅碰撞？我唔小心掂到佢，佢可以屈我打佢，然後走去同我哋d阿姐（稽核員）投訴我，點解我差d比佢非禮就唔可以講出嚟？仲要要脅我唔準講出去！
話就話我同佢係唔同部門（我係管核部，佢係舖頭嘅老細，不過佢係業務經理之下），唔可以用下屬身分投訴佢，但係我可以直接同業理投訴，亦可以選擇send e-mail或者直接用fax將佢做過嘅衰野講比總部聽，但係我唔想做到呢一步，我寫得出呢段野，就己經算係最後通牒，但係如果佢做嘅野更加過份嘅話我就直接喺大家樂集團個page，以管核文員身份直接投訴佢😠
ps：得罪文員係危險過得罪其他人，尤其是如果嗰間舖嘅文員曾經係物理老師嘅話就更加危險，因為永遠唔會知道我哋會用咩方法對付得罪我哋嘅人。
#metoo
#性騷擾
#受害者
name: 櫻井純

stop_filter_tweet: 呢件事我上個星期己經想講，但係等到而家先至得閒少少去講出嚟。。。 我係重慶大廈嗰間大家樂嘅管核文員，我留左喺呢間分店大約三個半月（我算留得耐，呢間舖之前有段時間係一個月換一個文員），入職第一個星期喺黃埔一期嗰間受訓，之後到左8月27日就去左重慶大廈嘅分店，頭一個月仲有個高級文員喺度嗰時個經理都未會做d性騷擾行為，亦唔會亂咁叫我做d文員絕對唔可以做嘅野，例如將宣傳物料同原材料由7樓倉搬落去舖頭，亦唔會喺圍數（即係數夾萬入面嘅錢）嗰時借意「i」埋去我個身度。 我嗰間舖嘅office係細過劏房好多，坐兩個人己經好逼，三個人（我、高級文員同經理）更加逼，但係經理都唔會「i」個身埋去高級文員嗰度。 呢一個月，亦係唯一一個月冇比個經理亂搞我嘅時間。 自從高級文員比人調左去另一間舖，而我又正式接手嗰度之後，個pk經理（唔係副經理，係正嗰個經理，男人）就開始愈嚟愈過分，例如喺我同佢都喺office嗰陣時特登「i」埋去我個身度，圍數嗰陣又趁我好專心計數嗰時成個頭拱埋去我隻手度，你i埋去我個身度，我可以當係因為office太細而要咁樣做，但係成個死人頭拱埋去我隻手度又點解釋？前世未見過理科生計數定係未見過計數計得咁快嘅文員？不過高級文員同樣計數計得快，又唔見佢拱個死人頭埋去！我就反而比佢咁樣對待！呢d行為可能對於佢嚟講好正常，但係根本就係有意去非禮人！ 我己經冇同佢講我係理科生，亦冇同佢講我算係一個物理科老師，我唔想運用我嘅物理知識去對付一個色狼，而家最慘係個cctv一直都影到佢冇非禮我，但係佢成日都hi到我個身，甚至有時差d掂到我個胸，咁呢d叫咩？唔通又係普通嘅碰撞？我唔小心掂到佢，佢可以屈我打佢，然後走去同我哋d阿姐（稽核員）投訴我，點解我差d比佢非禮就唔可以講出嚟？仲要要脅我唔準講出去！ 話就話我同佢係唔同部門（我係管核部，佢係舖頭嘅老細，不過佢係業務經理之下），唔可以用下屬身分投訴佢，但係我可以直接同業理投訴，亦可以選擇send e-mail或者直接用fax將佢做過嘅衰野講比總部聽，但係我唔想做到呢一步，我寫得出呢段野，就己經算係最後通牒，但係如果佢做嘅野更加過份嘅話我就直接喺大家樂集團個page，以管核文員身份直接投訴佢😠 ps：得罪文員係危險過得罪其他人，尤其是如果嗰間舖嘅文員曾經係物理老師嘅話就更加危險，因為永遠唔會知道我哋會用咩方法對付得罪我哋嘅人。 etoo 騷擾

text:
alright snowflakes this is for you!!! you all wanna ruin christmas banning rudolph and baby it’s cold outside and charlie brown thanksgiving!!! go full force and pull all these songs then too you candy asses!!!! but know i will always and play every one of these songs on my talk show and in my performances, and please come and tell me how offended you are so i can tell you to go have a silent night!!!!!!!! #1) i saw mommy kissing santa claus: subjecting minors to softcore porn

#2) the christmas song: open fire? pollution. folks dressed up like eskimos? cultural appropriation 
#3) holly jolly christmas: kiss her once for me? unwanted advances

#4) white christmas? : racist

#5) santa claus is coming to town: sees you when you’re sleeping? knows when you’re awake? peeping tom stalker

#6) most wonderful time of the year: everyone telling you be of good cheer? forced to hide depression

#7) rudolph: bullying

#8) it’s beginning to look a lot like christmas: forced gender-specific gifts. dolls for janice & jen. boots & pistols (omg guns)! for barney & ben.

#9) santa baby: good digger, blackmail

#10) frosty the snowman: sexist, not a snow woman

#11) do you hear what i hear: blatant disregard for the deaf

#12) have yourself a merry little christmas: make the yuletide gay? wow, just wow!

#13) jingle bell rock: giddy up jingle horse, pick up your feet. animal abuse

#14) winter wonderland: parson brown demanding they get married....forced partnership.

#15) i’ll be home for christmas: not if you’re homeless. that’s just insensitive 
#16) grandma got run over by a reindeer: homicide. extreme violence and promotes alcoholism 
there’s prob many more. this isn’t my list but a list i came across.

enough with this me too and how about up yours. oh sorry that could be taken as sexual too.

again i’m against forced relations and rape and all that stuff but we are in 2018. for god’s sake there’s never been an issue before with programming and christmas songs before. 
why are giving in to these snowflakes because you want to keep listeners.....really i never even knew cbc radio had listeners?! like come on!!!!!!! #metoo #christmas #songs #leavechristmasalone

girl power - new group exhibition, now on artsy: "while art history is rich with representations of submissive, nude women for the pleasure of male artists, patrons and collectors, the new group exhibition 'girl power' wishes to offer a new perspective of female empowerment and motivation, with over 50 artworks by 18 artists". www.artsy.net/israeli-art-in-los-angeles

#repost @amberheardit
“#amberheard talks about 'reckless’ women, ‘boring’ female film roles and why hollywood needs to change now 'i don't want things to stay the same, do you?' 'i get sick of the damsel in distress narrative as much as anyone, maybe, considering this is my line of work, perhaps more. the average viewer doesn't want to see the same formulaic approach that's outdated and two-dimensional and represents women in a very narrow light. it's boring and un-compelling for, not just a female audience, but for men as well.' 'the fact that so many women have said either timesup, or enough is enough, or #metoo, there's a reason we're all saying the same thing. we don't want things to stay the same. 'anybody who identifies as a woman understands a certain way of living through a filter, and that filter is important to recognise so we can change it, so we can challenge it, so we can test its integrity, and so we can apply, in future, lenses that are more fortified or of different colours for our daughters and our sisters moving forward.’
#unitednations #humanrights #standup4humanrights #timesupnow #timesup”
@amberheard
#mera #queenmera #aquaman #istandwithamber #wearewithyouamberheard

text:
congratulations to ada hegerberg  who won the ballon d’or 2018
.
ada’s historic moment overshadowed by dj martin solveig asking if she could twerk? what? the first ever woman to win this prestigious award and we find habitual sexism at its best? solveig has since apologised saying it was just a joke and his words were a distortion of his english culture level? no this is ‘unconscious’ habitual sexism mr solveig and the more we acknowledge such everyday sexism, the more seriously women will be considered as equals. .
at future female our mission is to give women and girls tools to respond to sexist behaviour, conscious and unconscious, often seen as a joke, banter or so subtle it’s ignored and condoned. .
.
still think it’s a joke? 👇🏼👇🏼👇🏼
@andymurray says ‘it wasn’t a joke, this level of sexism is unreal’ .

everyday equality is what we at future female seek and promote, through everyday language. .
.
